1543/// Fold icmp (and (sh X, Y), C2), C1.
1544Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpAndShift(ICmpInst &Cmp, BinaryOperator *And,
1545 const APInt &C1, const APInt &C2) {
1546 BinaryOperator *Shift = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(And->getOperand(0));
1547 if (!Shift || !Shift->isShift())
1548 return nullptr;
1549
1550 // If this is: (X >> C3) & C2 != C1 (where any shift and any compare could
1551 // exist), turn it into (X & (C2 << C3)) != (C1 << C3). This happens a LOT in
1552 // code produced by the clang front-end, for bitfield access.
1553 // This seemingly simple opportunity to fold away a shift turns out to be
1554 // rather complicated. See PR17827 for details.
1555 unsigned ShiftOpcode = Shift->getOpcode();
1556 bool IsShl = ShiftOpcode == Instruction::Shl;
1557 const APInt *C3;
1558 if (match(Shift->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C3))) {
1559 bool CanFold = false;
1560 if (ShiftOpcode == Instruction::Shl) {
1561 // For a left shift, we can fold if the comparison is not signed. We can
1562 // also fold a signed comparison if the mask value and comparison value
1563 // are not negative. These constraints may not be obvious, but we can
1564 // prove that they are correct using an SMT solver.
1565 if (!Cmp.isSigned() || (!C2.isNegative() && !C1.isNegative()))
1566 CanFold = true;
1567 } else {
1568 bool IsAshr = ShiftOpcode == Instruction::AShr;
1569 // For a logical right shift, we can fold if the comparison is not signed.
1570 // We can also fold a signed comparison if the shifted mask value and the
1571 // shifted comparison value are not negative. These constraints may not be
1572 // obvious, but we can prove that they are correct using an SMT solver.
1573 // For an arithmetic shift right we can do the same, if we ensure
1574 // the And doesn't use any bits being shifted in. Normally these would
1575 // be turned into lshr by SimplifyDemandedBits, but not if there is an
1576 // additional user.
1577 if (!IsAshr || (C2.shl(*C3).lshr(*C3) == C2)) {
1578 if (!Cmp.isSigned() ||
1579 (!C2.shl(*C3).isNegative() && !C1.shl(*C3).isNegative()))
1580 CanFold = true;
1581 }
1582 }
1583
1584 if (CanFold) {
1585 APInt NewCst = IsShl ? C1.lshr(*C3) : C1.shl(*C3);
1586 APInt SameAsC1 = IsShl ? NewCst.shl(*C3) : NewCst.lshr(*C3);
1587 // Check to see if we are shifting out any of the bits being compared.
1588 if (SameAsC1 != C1) {
1589 // If we shifted bits out, the fold is not going to work out. As a
1590 // special case, check to see if this means that the result is always
1591 // true or false now.
1592 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
1593 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, ConstantInt::getFalse(Cmp.getType()));
1594 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)
1595 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, ConstantInt::getTrue(Cmp.getType()));
1596 } else {
1597 Cmp.setOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(And->getType(), NewCst));
1598 APInt NewAndCst = IsShl ? C2.lshr(*C3) : C2.shl(*C3);
1599 And->setOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(And->getType(), NewAndCst));
1600 And->setOperand(0, Shift->getOperand(0));
1601 Worklist.Add(Shift); // Shift is dead.
1602 return &Cmp;
1603 }
1604 }
1605 }
1606
1607 // Turn ((X >> Y) & C2) == 0 into (X & (C2 << Y)) == 0. The latter is
1608 // preferable because it allows the C2 << Y expression to be hoisted out of a
1609 // loop if Y is invariant and X is not.
1610 if (Shift->hasOneUse() && C1.isNullValue() && Cmp.isEquality() &&
1611 !Shift->isArithmeticShift() && !isa<Constant>(Shift->getOperand(0))) {
1612 // Compute C2 << Y.
1613 Value *NewShift =
1614 IsShl ? Builder.CreateLShr(And->getOperand(1), Shift->getOperand(1))
1615 : Builder.CreateShl(And->getOperand(1), Shift->getOperand(1));
1616
1617 // Compute X & (C2 << Y).
1618 Value *NewAnd = Builder.CreateAnd(Shift->getOperand(0), NewShift);
1619 Cmp.setOperand(0, NewAnd);
1620 return &Cmp;
1621 }
1622
1623 return nullptr;
1624}
1625
1626/// Fold icmp (and X, C2), C1.
1627Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpAndConstConst(ICmpInst &Cmp,
1628 BinaryOperator *And,
1629 const APInt &C1) {
1630 // For vectors: icmp ne (and X, 1), 0 --> trunc X to N x i1
1631 // TODO: We canonicalize to the longer form for scalars because we have
1632 // better analysis/folds for icmp, and codegen may be better with icmp.
1633 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == CmpInst::ICMP_NE && Cmp.getType()->isVectorTy() &&
1634 C1.isNullValue() && match(And->getOperand(1), m_One()))
1635 return new TruncInst(And->getOperand(0), Cmp.getType());
1636
1637 const APInt *C2;
1638 if (!match(And->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C2)))
1639 return nullptr;
1640
1641 if (!And->hasOneUse())
1642 return nullptr;
1643
1644 // If the LHS is an 'and' of a truncate and we can widen the and/compare to
1645 // the input width without changing the value produced, eliminate the cast:
1646 //
1647 // icmp (and (trunc W), C2), C1 -> icmp (and W, C2'), C1'
1648 //
1649 // We can do this transformation if the constants do not have their sign bits
1650 // set or if it is an equality comparison. Extending a relational comparison
1651 // when we're checking the sign bit would not work.
1652 Value *W;
1653 if (match(And->getOperand(0), m_OneUse(m_Trunc(m_Value(W)))) &&
1654 (Cmp.isEquality() || (!C1.isNegative() && !C2->isNegative()))) {
1655 // TODO: Is this a good transform for vectors? Wider types may reduce
1656 // throughput. Should this transform be limited (even for scalars) by using
1657 // shouldChangeType()?
1658 if (!Cmp.getType()->isVectorTy()) {
1659 Type *WideType = W->getType();
1660 unsigned WideScalarBits = WideType->getScalarSizeInBits();
1661 Constant *ZextC1 = ConstantInt::get(WideType, C1.zext(WideScalarBits));
1662 Constant *ZextC2 = ConstantInt::get(WideType, C2->zext(WideScalarBits));
1663 Value *NewAnd = Builder.CreateAnd(W, ZextC2, And->getName());
1664 return new ICmpInst(Cmp.getPredicate(), NewAnd, ZextC1);
1665 }
1666 }
1667
1668 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpAndShift(Cmp, And, C1, *C2))
1669 return I;
1670
1671 // (icmp pred (and (or (lshr A, B), A), 1), 0) -->
1672 // (icmp pred (and A, (or (shl 1, B), 1), 0))
1673 //
1674 // iff pred isn't signed
1675 if (!Cmp.isSigned() && C1.isNullValue() && And->getOperand(0)->hasOneUse() &&
1676 match(And->getOperand(1), m_One())) {
1677 Constant *One = cast<Constant>(And->getOperand(1));
1678 Value *Or = And->getOperand(0);
1679 Value *A, *B, *LShr;
1680 if (match(Or, m_Or(m_Value(LShr), m_Value(A))) &&
1681 match(LShr, m_LShr(m_Specific(A), m_Value(B)))) {
1682 unsigned UsesRemoved = 0;
1683 if (And->hasOneUse())
1684 ++UsesRemoved;
1685 if (Or->hasOneUse())
1686 ++UsesRemoved;
1687 if (LShr->hasOneUse())
1688 ++UsesRemoved;
1689
1690 // Compute A & ((1 << B) | 1)
1691 Value *NewOr = nullptr;
1692 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(B)) {
1693 if (UsesRemoved >= 1)
1694 NewOr = ConstantExpr::getOr(ConstantExpr::getNUWShl(One, C), One);
1695 } else {
1696 if (UsesRemoved >= 3)
1697 NewOr = Builder.CreateOr(Builder.CreateShl(One, B, LShr->getName(),
1698 /*HasNUW=*/true),
1699 One, Or->getName());
1700 }
1701 if (NewOr) {
1702 Value *NewAnd = Builder.CreateAnd(A, NewOr, And->getName());
1703 Cmp.setOperand(0, NewAnd);
1704 return &Cmp;
1705 }
1706 }
1707 }
1708
1709 return nullptr;
1710}
1711
1712/// Fold icmp (and X, Y), C.
1713Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpAndConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
1714 BinaryOperator *And,
1715 const APInt &C) {
1716 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpAndConstConst(Cmp, And, C))
1717 return I;
1718
1719 // TODO: These all require that Y is constant too, so refactor with the above.
1720
1721 // Try to optimize things like "A[i] & 42 == 0" to index computations.
1722 Value *X = And->getOperand(0);
1723 Value *Y = And->getOperand(1);
1724 if (auto *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(X))
1725 if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LI->getOperand(0)))
1726 if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GEP->getOperand(0)))
1727 if (GV->isConstant() && GV->hasDefinitiveInitializer() &&
1728 !LI->isVolatile() && isa<ConstantInt>(Y)) {
1729 ConstantInt *C2 = cast<ConstantInt>(Y);
1730 if (Instruction *Res = foldCmpLoadFromIndexedGlobal(GEP, GV, Cmp, C2))
1731 return Res;
1732 }
1733
1734 if (!Cmp.isEquality())
1735 return nullptr;
1736
1737 // X & -C == -C -> X > u ~C
1738 // X & -C != -C -> X <= u ~C
1739 // iff C is a power of 2
1740 if (Cmp.getOperand(1) == Y && (-C).isPowerOf2()) {
1741 auto NewPred = Cmp.getPredicate() == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? CmpInst::ICMP_UGT
1742 : CmpInst::ICMP_ULE;
1743 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, X, SubOne(cast<Constant>(Cmp.getOperand(1))));
1744 }
1745
1746 // (X & C2) == 0 -> (trunc X) >= 0
1747 // (X & C2) != 0 -> (trunc X) < 0
1748 // iff C2 is a power of 2 and it masks the sign bit of a legal integer type.
1749 const APInt *C2;
1750 if (And->hasOneUse() && C.isNullValue() && match(Y, m_APInt(C2))) {
1751 int32_t ExactLogBase2 = C2->exactLogBase2();
1752 if (ExactLogBase2 != -1 && DL.isLegalInteger(ExactLogBase2 + 1)) {
1753 Type *NTy = IntegerType::get(Cmp.getContext(), ExactLogBase2 + 1);
1754 if (And->getType()->isVectorTy())
1755 NTy = VectorType::get(NTy, And->getType()->getVectorNumElements());
1756 Value *Trunc = Builder.CreateTrunc(X, NTy);
1757 auto NewPred = Cmp.getPredicate() == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? CmpInst::ICMP_SGE
1758 : CmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
1759 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, Trunc, Constant::getNullValue(NTy));
1760 }
1761 }
1762
1763 return nullptr;
1764}
1765
1766/// Fold icmp (or X, Y), C.
1767Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpOrConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp, BinaryOperator *Or,
1768 const APInt &C) {
1769 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
1770 if (C.isOneValue()) {
1771 // icmp slt signum(V) 1 --> icmp slt V, 1
1772 Value *V = nullptr;
1773 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(Or, m_Signum(m_Value(V))))
1774 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, V,
1775 ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), 1));
1776 }
1777
1778 Value *OrOp0 = Or->getOperand(0), *OrOp1 = Or->getOperand(1);
1779 if (Cmp.isEquality() && Cmp.getOperand(1) == OrOp1) {
1780 // X | C == C --> X <=u C
1781 // X | C != C --> X >u C
1782 // iff C+1 is a power of 2 (C is a bitmask of the low bits)
1783 if ((C + 1).isPowerOf2()) {
1784 Pred = (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ) ? CmpInst::ICMP_ULE : CmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
1785 return new ICmpInst(Pred, OrOp0, OrOp1);
1786 }
1787 // More general: are all bits outside of a mask constant set or not set?
1788 // X | C == C --> (X & ~C) == 0
1789 // X | C != C --> (X & ~C) != 0
1790 if (Or->hasOneUse()) {
1791 Value *A = Builder.CreateAnd(OrOp0, ~C);
1792 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, ConstantInt::getNullValue(OrOp0->getType()));
1793 }
1794 }
1795
1796 if (!Cmp.isEquality() || !C.isNullValue() || !Or->hasOneUse())
1797 return nullptr;
1798
1799 Value *P, *Q;
1800 if (match(Or, m_Or(m_PtrToInt(m_Value(P)), m_PtrToInt(m_Value(Q))))) {
1801 // Simplify icmp eq (or (ptrtoint P), (ptrtoint Q)), 0
1802 // -> and (icmp eq P, null), (icmp eq Q, null).
1803 Value *CmpP =
1804 Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, P, ConstantInt::getNullValue(P->getType()));
1805 Value *CmpQ =
1806 Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, Q, ConstantInt::getNullValue(Q->getType()));
1807 auto BOpc = Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? Instruction::And : Instruction::Or;
1808 return BinaryOperator::Create(BOpc, CmpP, CmpQ);
1809 }
1810
1811 // Are we using xors to bitwise check for a pair of (in)equalities? Convert to
1812 // a shorter form that has more potential to be folded even further.
1813 Value *X1, *X2, *X3, *X4;
1814 if (match(OrOp0, m_OneUse(m_Xor(m_Value(X1), m_Value(X2)))) &&
1815 match(OrOp1, m_OneUse(m_Xor(m_Value(X3), m_Value(X4))))) {
1816 // ((X1 ^ X2) || (X3 ^ X4)) == 0 --> (X1 == X2) && (X3 == X4)
1817 // ((X1 ^ X2) || (X3 ^ X4)) != 0 --> (X1 != X2) || (X3 != X4)
1818 Value *Cmp12 = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, X1, X2);
1819 Value *Cmp34 = Builder.CreateICmp(Pred, X3, X4);
1820 auto BOpc = Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? Instruction::And : Instruction::Or;
1821 return BinaryOperator::Create(BOpc, Cmp12, Cmp34);
1822 }
1823
1824 return nullptr;
1825}
1826
1827/// Fold icmp (mul X, Y), C.
1828Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpMulConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
1829 BinaryOperator *Mul,
1830 const APInt &C) {
1831 const APInt *MulC;
1832 if (!match(Mul->getOperand(1), m_APInt(MulC)))
1833 return nullptr;
1834
1835 // If this is a test of the sign bit and the multiply is sign-preserving with
1836 // a constant operand, use the multiply LHS operand instead.
1837 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
1838 if (isSignTest(Pred, C) && Mul->hasNoSignedWrap()) {
1839 if (MulC->isNegative())
1840 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
1841 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Mul->getOperand(0),
1842 Constant::getNullValue(Mul->getType()));
1843 }
1844
1845 return nullptr;
1846}
1847
1848/// Fold icmp (shl 1, Y), C.
1849static Instruction *foldICmpShlOne(ICmpInst &Cmp, Instruction *Shl,
1850 const APInt &C) {
1851 Value *Y;
1852 if (!match(Shl, m_Shl(m_One(), m_Value(Y))))
1853 return nullptr;
1854
1855 Type *ShiftType = Shl->getType();
1856 unsigned TypeBits = C.getBitWidth();
1857 bool CIsPowerOf2 = C.isPowerOf2();
1858 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
1859 if (Cmp.isUnsigned()) {
1860 // (1 << Y) pred C -> Y pred Log2(C)
1861 if (!CIsPowerOf2) {
1862 // (1 << Y) < 30 -> Y <= 4
1863 // (1 << Y) <= 30 -> Y <= 4
1864 // (1 << Y) >= 30 -> Y > 4
1865 // (1 << Y) > 30 -> Y > 4
1866 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
1867 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE;
1868 else if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
1869 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
1870 }
1871
1872 // (1 << Y) >= 2147483648 -> Y >= 31 -> Y == 31
1873 // (1 << Y) < 2147483648 -> Y < 31 -> Y != 31
1874 unsigned CLog2 = C.logBase2();
1875 if (CLog2 == TypeBits - 1) {
1876 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
1877 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
1878 else if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
1879 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
1880 }
1881 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Y, ConstantInt::get(ShiftType, CLog2));
1882 } else if (Cmp.isSigned()) {
1883 Constant *BitWidthMinusOne = ConstantInt::get(ShiftType, TypeBits - 1);
1884 if (C.isAllOnesValue()) {
1885 // (1 << Y) <= -1 -> Y == 31
1886 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
1887 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Y, BitWidthMinusOne);
1888
1889 // (1 << Y) > -1 -> Y != 31
1890 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
1891 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Y, BitWidthMinusOne);
1892 } else if (!C) {
1893 // (1 << Y) < 0 -> Y == 31
1894 // (1 << Y) <= 0 -> Y == 31
1895 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
1896 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Y, BitWidthMinusOne);
1897
1898 // (1 << Y) >= 0 -> Y != 31
1899 // (1 << Y) > 0 -> Y != 31
1900 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
1901 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Y, BitWidthMinusOne);
1902 }
1903 } else if (Cmp.isEquality() && CIsPowerOf2) {
1904 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Y, ConstantInt::get(ShiftType, C.logBase2()));
1905 }
1906
1907 return nullptr;
1908}
1909
1910/// Fold icmp (shl X, Y), C.
1911Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpShlConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
1912 BinaryOperator *Shl,
1913 const APInt &C) {
1914 const APInt *ShiftVal;
1915 if (Cmp.isEquality() && match(Shl->getOperand(0), m_APInt(ShiftVal)))
1916 return foldICmpShlConstConst(Cmp, Shl->getOperand(1), C, *ShiftVal);
1917
1918 const APInt *ShiftAmt;
1919 if (!match(Shl->getOperand(1), m_APInt(ShiftAmt)))
1920 return foldICmpShlOne(Cmp, Shl, C);
1921
1922 // Check that the shift amount is in range. If not, don't perform undefined
1923 // shifts. When the shift is visited, it will be simplified.
1924 unsigned TypeBits = C.getBitWidth();
1925 if (ShiftAmt->uge(TypeBits))
1926 return nullptr;
1927
1928 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
1929 Value *X = Shl->getOperand(0);
1930 Type *ShType = Shl->getType();
1931
1932 // NSW guarantees that we are only shifting out sign bits from the high bits,
1933 // so we can ASHR the compare constant without needing a mask and eliminate
1934 // the shift.
1935 if (Shl->hasNoSignedWrap()) {
1936 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT) {
1937 // icmp Pred (shl nsw X, ShiftAmt), C --> icmp Pred X, (C >>s ShiftAmt)
1938 APInt ShiftedC = C.ashr(*ShiftAmt);
1939 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1940 }
1941 if ((Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE) &&
1942 C.ashr(*ShiftAmt).shl(*ShiftAmt) == C) {
1943 APInt ShiftedC = C.ashr(*ShiftAmt);
1944 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1945 }
1946 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT) {
1947 // SLE is the same as above, but SLE is canonicalized to SLT, so convert:
1948 // (X << S) <=s C is equiv to X <=s (C >> S) for all C
1949 // (X << S) <s (C + 1) is equiv to X <s (C >> S) + 1 if C <s SMAX
1950 // (X << S) <s C is equiv to X <s ((C - 1) >> S) + 1 if C >s SMIN
1951 assert(!C.isMinSignedValue() && "Unexpected icmp slt");
1952 APInt ShiftedC = (C - 1).ashr(*ShiftAmt) + 1;
1953 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1954 }
1955 // If this is a signed comparison to 0 and the shift is sign preserving,
1956 // use the shift LHS operand instead; isSignTest may change 'Pred', so only
1957 // do that if we're sure to not continue on in this function.
1958 if (isSignTest(Pred, C))
1959 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, Constant::getNullValue(ShType));
1960 }
1961
1962 // NUW guarantees that we are only shifting out zero bits from the high bits,
1963 // so we can LSHR the compare constant without needing a mask and eliminate
1964 // the shift.
1965 if (Shl->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) {
1966 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT) {
1967 // icmp Pred (shl nuw X, ShiftAmt), C --> icmp Pred X, (C >>u ShiftAmt)
1968 APInt ShiftedC = C.lshr(*ShiftAmt);
1969 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1970 }
1971 if ((Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE) &&
1972 C.lshr(*ShiftAmt).shl(*ShiftAmt) == C) {
1973 APInt ShiftedC = C.lshr(*ShiftAmt);
1974 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1975 }
1976 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT) {
1977 // ULE is the same as above, but ULE is canonicalized to ULT, so convert:
1978 // (X << S) <=u C is equiv to X <=u (C >> S) for all C
1979 // (X << S) <u (C + 1) is equiv to X <u (C >> S) + 1 if C <u ~0u
1980 // (X << S) <u C is equiv to X <u ((C - 1) >> S) + 1 if C >u 0
1981 assert(C.ugt(0) && "ult 0 should have been eliminated");
1982 APInt ShiftedC = (C - 1).lshr(*ShiftAmt) + 1;
1983 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShType, ShiftedC));
1984 }
1985 }
1986
1987 if (Cmp.isEquality() && Shl->hasOneUse()) {
1988 // Strength-reduce the shift into an 'and'.
1989 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(
1990 ShType,
1991 APInt::getLowBitsSet(TypeBits, TypeBits - ShiftAmt->getZExtValue()));
1992 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(X, Mask, Shl->getName() + ".mask");
1993 Constant *LShrC = ConstantInt::get(ShType, C.lshr(*ShiftAmt));
1994 return new ICmpInst(Pred, And, LShrC);
1995 }
1996
1997 // Otherwise, if this is a comparison of the sign bit, simplify to and/test.
1998 bool TrueIfSigned = false;
1999 if (Shl->hasOneUse() && isSignBitCheck(Pred, C, TrueIfSigned)) {
2000 // (X << 31) <s 0 --> (X & 1) != 0
2001 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(
2002 ShType,
2003 APInt::getOneBitSet(TypeBits, TypeBits - ShiftAmt->getZExtValue() - 1));
2004 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(X, Mask, Shl->getName() + ".mask");
2005 return new ICmpInst(TrueIfSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_NE : ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ,
2006 And, Constant::getNullValue(ShType));
2007 }
2008
2009 // Transform (icmp pred iM (shl iM %v, N), C)
2010 // -> (icmp pred i(M-N) (trunc %v iM to i(M-N)), (trunc (C>>N))
2011 // Transform the shl to a trunc if (trunc (C>>N)) has no loss and M-N.
2012 // This enables us to get rid of the shift in favor of a trunc that may be
2013 // free on the target. It has the additional benefit of comparing to a
2014 // smaller constant that may be more target-friendly.
2015 unsigned Amt = ShiftAmt->getLimitedValue(TypeBits - 1);
2016 if (Shl->hasOneUse() && Amt != 0 && C.countTrailingZeros() >= Amt &&
2017 DL.isLegalInteger(TypeBits - Amt)) {
2018 Type *TruncTy = IntegerType::get(Cmp.getContext(), TypeBits - Amt);
2019 if (ShType->isVectorTy())
2020 TruncTy = VectorType::get(TruncTy, ShType->getVectorNumElements());
2021 Constant *NewC =
2022 ConstantInt::get(TruncTy, C.ashr(*ShiftAmt).trunc(TypeBits - Amt));
2023 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Builder.CreateTrunc(X, TruncTy), NewC);
2024 }
2025
2026 return nullptr;
2027}
2028
2029/// Fold icmp ({al}shr X, Y), C.
2030Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpShrConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2031 BinaryOperator *Shr,
2032 const APInt &C) {
2033 // An exact shr only shifts out zero bits, so:
2034 // icmp eq/ne (shr X, Y), 0 --> icmp eq/ne X, 0
2035 Value *X = Shr->getOperand(0);
2036 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2037 if (Cmp.isEquality() && Shr->isExact() && Shr->hasOneUse() &&
2038 C.isNullValue())
2039 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, Cmp.getOperand(1));
2040
2041 const APInt *ShiftVal;
2042 if (Cmp.isEquality() && match(Shr->getOperand(0), m_APInt(ShiftVal)))
2043 return foldICmpShrConstConst(Cmp, Shr->getOperand(1), C, *ShiftVal);
2044
2045 const APInt *ShiftAmt;
2046 if (!match(Shr->getOperand(1), m_APInt(ShiftAmt)))
2047 return nullptr;
2048
2049 // Check that the shift amount is in range. If not, don't perform undefined
2050 // shifts. When the shift is visited it will be simplified.
2051 unsigned TypeBits = C.getBitWidth();
2052 unsigned ShAmtVal = ShiftAmt->getLimitedValue(TypeBits);
2053 if (ShAmtVal >= TypeBits || ShAmtVal == 0)
2054 return nullptr;
2055
2056 bool IsAShr = Shr->getOpcode() == Instruction::AShr;
2057 bool IsExact = Shr->isExact();
2058 Type *ShrTy = Shr->getType();
2059 // TODO: If we could guarantee that InstSimplify would handle all of the
2060 // constant-value-based preconditions in the folds below, then we could assert
2061 // those conditions rather than checking them. This is difficult because of
2062 // undef/poison (PR34838).
2063 if (IsAShr) {
2064 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT || (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && IsExact)) {
2065 // icmp slt (ashr X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp slt X, (C << ShAmtC)
2066 // icmp sgt (ashr exact X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp sgt X, (C << ShAmtC)
2067 APInt ShiftedC = C.shl(ShAmtVal);
2068 if (ShiftedC.ashr(ShAmtVal) == C)
2069 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, ShiftedC));
2070 }
2071 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT) {
2072 // icmp sgt (ashr X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp sgt X, ((C + 1) << ShAmtC) - 1
2073 APInt ShiftedC = (C + 1).shl(ShAmtVal) - 1;
2074 if (!C.isMaxSignedValue() && !(C + 1).shl(ShAmtVal).isMinSignedValue() &&
2075 (ShiftedC + 1).ashr(ShAmtVal) == (C + 1))
2076 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, ShiftedC));
2077 }
2078 } else {
2079 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT || (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT && IsExact)) {
2080 // icmp ult (lshr X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp ult X, (C << ShAmtC)
2081 // icmp ugt (lshr exact X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp ugt X, (C << ShAmtC)
2082 APInt ShiftedC = C.shl(ShAmtVal);
2083 if (ShiftedC.lshr(ShAmtVal) == C)
2084 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, ShiftedC));
2085 }
2086 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT) {
2087 // icmp ugt (lshr X, ShAmtC), C --> icmp ugt X, ((C + 1) << ShAmtC) - 1
2088 APInt ShiftedC = (C + 1).shl(ShAmtVal) - 1;
2089 if ((ShiftedC + 1).lshr(ShAmtVal) == (C + 1))
2090 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, ShiftedC));
2091 }
2092 }
2093
2094 if (!Cmp.isEquality())
2095 return nullptr;
2096
2097 // Handle equality comparisons of shift-by-constant.
2098
2099 // If the comparison constant changes with the shift, the comparison cannot
2100 // succeed (bits of the comparison constant cannot match the shifted value).
2101 // This should be known by InstSimplify and already be folded to true/false.
2102 assert(((IsAShr && C.shl(ShAmtVal).ashr(ShAmtVal) == C) ||
2103 (!IsAShr && C.shl(ShAmtVal).lshr(ShAmtVal) == C)) &&
2104 "Expected icmp+shr simplify did not occur.");
2105
2106 // If the bits shifted out are known zero, compare the unshifted value:
2107 // (X & 4) >> 1 == 2 --> (X & 4) == 4.
2108 if (Shr->isExact())
2109 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, C << ShAmtVal));
2110
2111 if (Shr->hasOneUse()) {
2112 // Canonicalize the shift into an 'and':
2113 // icmp eq/ne (shr X, ShAmt), C --> icmp eq/ne (and X, HiMask), (C << ShAmt)
2114 APInt Val(APInt::getHighBitsSet(TypeBits, TypeBits - ShAmtVal));
2115 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, Val);
2116 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(X, Mask, Shr->getName() + ".mask");
2117 return new ICmpInst(Pred, And, ConstantInt::get(ShrTy, C << ShAmtVal));
2118 }
2119
2120 return nullptr;
2121}
2122
2123/// Fold icmp (udiv X, Y), C.
2124Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpUDivConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2125 BinaryOperator *UDiv,
2126 const APInt &C) {
2127 const APInt *C2;
2128 if (!match(UDiv->getOperand(0), m_APInt(C2)))
2129 return nullptr;
2130
2131 assert(*C2 != 0 && "udiv 0, X should have been simplified already.");
2132
2133 // (icmp ugt (udiv C2, Y), C) -> (icmp ule Y, C2/(C+1))
2134 Value *Y = UDiv->getOperand(1);
2135 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT) {
2136 assert(!C.isMaxValue() &&
2137 "icmp ugt X, UINT_MAX should have been simplified already.");
2138 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE, Y,
2139 ConstantInt::get(Y->getType(), C2->udiv(C + 1)));
2140 }
2141
2142 // (icmp ult (udiv C2, Y), C) -> (icmp ugt Y, C2/C)
2143 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT) {
2144 assert(C != 0 && "icmp ult X, 0 should have been simplified already.");
2145 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT, Y,
2146 ConstantInt::get(Y->getType(), C2->udiv(C)));
2147 }
2148
2149 return nullptr;
2150}
2151
2152/// Fold icmp ({su}div X, Y), C.
2153Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpDivConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2154 BinaryOperator *Div,
2155 const APInt &C) {
2156 // Fold: icmp pred ([us]div X, C2), C -> range test
2157 // Fold this div into the comparison, producing a range check.
2158 // Determine, based on the divide type, what the range is being
2159 // checked. If there is an overflow on the low or high side, remember
2160 // it, otherwise compute the range [low, hi) bounding the new value.
2161 // See: InsertRangeTest above for the kinds of replacements possible.
2162 const APInt *C2;
2163 if (!match(Div->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C2)))
2164 return nullptr;
2165
2166 // FIXME: If the operand types don't match the type of the divide
2167 // then don't attempt this transform. The code below doesn't have the
2168 // logic to deal with a signed divide and an unsigned compare (and
2169 // vice versa). This is because (x /s C2) <s C produces different
2170 // results than (x /s C2) <u C or (x /u C2) <s C or even
2171 // (x /u C2) <u C. Simply casting the operands and result won't
2172 // work. :( The if statement below tests that condition and bails
2173 // if it finds it.
2174 bool DivIsSigned = Div->getOpcode() == Instruction::SDiv;
2175 if (!Cmp.isEquality() && DivIsSigned != Cmp.isSigned())
2176 return nullptr;
2177
2178 // The ProdOV computation fails on divide by 0 and divide by -1. Cases with
2179 // INT_MIN will also fail if the divisor is 1. Although folds of all these
2180 // division-by-constant cases should be present, we can not assert that they
2181 // have happened before we reach this icmp instruction.
2182 if (C2->isNullValue() || C2->isOneValue() ||
2183 (DivIsSigned && C2->isAllOnesValue()))
2184 return nullptr;
2185
2186 // Compute Prod = C * C2. We are essentially solving an equation of
2187 // form X / C2 = C. We solve for X by multiplying C2 and C.
2188 // By solving for X, we can turn this into a range check instead of computing
2189 // a divide.
2190 APInt Prod = C * *C2;
2191
2192 // Determine if the product overflows by seeing if the product is not equal to
2193 // the divide. Make sure we do the same kind of divide as in the LHS
2194 // instruction that we're folding.
2195 bool ProdOV = (DivIsSigned ? Prod.sdiv(*C2) : Prod.udiv(*C2)) != C;
2196
2197 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2198
2199 // If the division is known to be exact, then there is no remainder from the
2200 // divide, so the covered range size is unit, otherwise it is the divisor.
2201 APInt RangeSize = Div->isExact() ? APInt(C2->getBitWidth(), 1) : *C2;
2202
2203 // Figure out the interval that is being checked. For example, a comparison
2204 // like "X /u 5 == 0" is really checking that X is in the interval [0, 5).
2205 // Compute this interval based on the constants involved and the signedness of
2206 // the compare/divide. This computes a half-open interval, keeping track of
2207 // whether either value in the interval overflows. After analysis each
2208 // overflow variable is set to 0 if it's corresponding bound variable is valid
2209 // -1 if overflowed off the bottom end, or +1 if overflowed off the top end.
2210 int LoOverflow = 0, HiOverflow = 0;
2211 APInt LoBound, HiBound;
2212
2213 if (!DivIsSigned) { // udiv
2214 // e.g. X/5 op 3 --> [15, 20)
2215 LoBound = Prod;
2216 HiOverflow = LoOverflow = ProdOV;
2217 if (!HiOverflow) {
2218 // If this is not an exact divide, then many values in the range collapse
2219 // to the same result value.
2220 HiOverflow = addWithOverflow(HiBound, LoBound, RangeSize, false);
2221 }
2222 } else if (C2->isStrictlyPositive()) { // Divisor is > 0.
2223 if (C.isNullValue()) { // (X / pos) op 0
2224 // Can't overflow. e.g. X/2 op 0 --> [-1, 2)
2225 LoBound = -(RangeSize - 1);
2226 HiBound = RangeSize;
2227 } else if (C.isStrictlyPositive()) { // (X / pos) op pos
2228 LoBound = Prod; // e.g. X/5 op 3 --> [15, 20)
2229 HiOverflow = LoOverflow = ProdOV;
2230 if (!HiOverflow)
2231 HiOverflow = addWithOverflow(HiBound, Prod, RangeSize, true);
2232 } else { // (X / pos) op neg
2233 // e.g. X/5 op -3 --> [-15-4, -15+1) --> [-19, -14)
2234 HiBound = Prod + 1;
2235 LoOverflow = HiOverflow = ProdOV ? -1 : 0;
2236 if (!LoOverflow) {
2237 APInt DivNeg = -RangeSize;
2238 LoOverflow = addWithOverflow(LoBound, HiBound, DivNeg, true) ? -1 : 0;
2239 }
2240 }
2241 } else if (C2->isNegative()) { // Divisor is < 0.
2242 if (Div->isExact())
2243 RangeSize.negate();
2244 if (C.isNullValue()) { // (X / neg) op 0
2245 // e.g. X/-5 op 0 --> [-4, 5)
2246 LoBound = RangeSize + 1;
2247 HiBound = -RangeSize;
2248 if (HiBound == *C2) { // -INTMIN = INTMIN
2249 HiOverflow = 1; // [INTMIN+1, overflow)
2250 HiBound = APInt(); // e.g. X/INTMIN = 0 --> X > INTMIN
2251 }
2252 } else if (C.isStrictlyPositive()) { // (X / neg) op pos
2253 // e.g. X/-5 op 3 --> [-19, -14)
2254 HiBound = Prod + 1;
2255 HiOverflow = LoOverflow = ProdOV ? -1 : 0;
2256 if (!LoOverflow)
2257 LoOverflow = addWithOverflow(LoBound, HiBound, RangeSize, true) ? -1:0;
2258 } else { // (X / neg) op neg
2259 LoBound = Prod; // e.g. X/-5 op -3 --> [15, 20)
2260 LoOverflow = HiOverflow = ProdOV;
2261 if (!HiOverflow)
2262 HiOverflow = subWithOverflow(HiBound, Prod, RangeSize, true);
2263 }
2264
2265 // Dividing by a negative swaps the condition. LT <-> GT
2266 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
2267 }
2268
2269 Value *X = Div->getOperand(0);
2270 switch (Pred) {
2271 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled icmp opcode!");
2272 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
2273 if (LoOverflow && HiOverflow)
2274 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getFalse());
2275 if (HiOverflow)
2276 return new ICmpInst(DivIsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE :
2277 ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, X,
2278 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), LoBound));
2279 if (LoOverflow)
2280 return new ICmpInst(DivIsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT :
2281 ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, X,
2282 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), HiBound));
2283 return replaceInstUsesWith(
2284 Cmp, insertRangeTest(X, LoBound, HiBound, DivIsSigned, true));
2285 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
2286 if (LoOverflow && HiOverflow)
2287 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getTrue());
2288 if (HiOverflow)
2289 return new ICmpInst(DivIsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT :
2290 ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, X,
2291 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), LoBound));
2292 if (LoOverflow)
2293 return new ICmpInst(DivIsSigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE :
2294 ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, X,
2295 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), HiBound));
2296 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp,
2297 insertRangeTest(X, LoBound, HiBound,
2298 DivIsSigned, false));
2299 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
2300 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
2301 if (LoOverflow == +1) // Low bound is greater than input range.
2302 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getTrue());
2303 if (LoOverflow == -1) // Low bound is less than input range.
2304 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getFalse());
2305 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), LoBound));
2306 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
2307 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
2308 if (HiOverflow == +1) // High bound greater than input range.
2309 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getFalse());
2310 if (HiOverflow == -1) // High bound less than input range.
2311 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Builder.getTrue());
2312 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
2313 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, X,
2314 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), HiBound));
2315 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, X,
2316 ConstantInt::get(Div->getType(), HiBound));
2317 }
2318
2319 return nullptr;
2320}
2321
2322/// Fold icmp (sub X, Y), C.
2323Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpSubConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2324 BinaryOperator *Sub,
2325 const APInt &C) {
2326 Value *X = Sub->getOperand(0), *Y = Sub->getOperand(1);
2327 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2328 const APInt *C2;
2329 APInt SubResult;
2330
2331 // (icmp P (sub nuw|nsw C2, Y), C) -> (icmp swap(P) Y, C2-C)
2332 if (match(X, m_APInt(C2)) &&
2333 ((Cmp.isUnsigned() && Sub->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) ||
2334 (Cmp.isSigned() && Sub->hasNoSignedWrap())) &&
2335 !subWithOverflow(SubResult, *C2, C, Cmp.isSigned()))
2336 return new ICmpInst(Cmp.getSwappedPredicate(), Y,
2337 ConstantInt::get(Y->getType(), SubResult));
2338
2339 // The following transforms are only worth it if the only user of the subtract
2340 // is the icmp.
2341 if (!Sub->hasOneUse())
2342 return nullptr;
2343
2344 if (Sub->hasNoSignedWrap()) {
2345 // (icmp sgt (sub nsw X, Y), -1) -> (icmp sge X, Y)
2346 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C.isAllOnesValue())
2347 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, X, Y);
2348
2349 // (icmp sgt (sub nsw X, Y), 0) -> (icmp sgt X, Y)
2350 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C.isNullValue())
2351 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, X, Y);
2352
2353 // (icmp slt (sub nsw X, Y), 0) -> (icmp slt X, Y)
2354 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C.isNullValue())
2355 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, Y);
2356
2357 // (icmp slt (sub nsw X, Y), 1) -> (icmp sle X, Y)
2358 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C.isOneValue())
2359 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE, X, Y);
2360 }
2361
2362 if (!match(X, m_APInt(C2)))
2363 return nullptr;
2364
2365 // C2 - Y <u C -> (Y | (C - 1)) == C2
2366 // iff (C2 & (C - 1)) == C - 1 and C is a power of 2
2367 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && C.isPowerOf2() &&
2368 (*C2 & (C - 1)) == (C - 1))
2369 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Builder.CreateOr(Y, C - 1), X);
2370
2371 // C2 - Y >u C -> (Y | C) != C2
2372 // iff C2 & C == C and C + 1 is a power of 2
2373 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && (C + 1).isPowerOf2() && (*C2 & C) == C)
2374 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Builder.CreateOr(Y, C), X);
2375
2376 return nullptr;
2377}
2378
2379/// Fold icmp (add X, Y), C.
2380Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpAddConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2381 BinaryOperator *Add,
2382 const APInt &C) {
2383 Value *Y = Add->getOperand(1);
2384 const APInt *C2;
2385 if (Cmp.isEquality() || !match(Y, m_APInt(C2)))
2386 return nullptr;
2387
2388 // Fold icmp pred (add X, C2), C.
2389 Value *X = Add->getOperand(0);
2390 Type *Ty = Add->getType();
2391 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2392
2393 if (!Add->hasOneUse())
2394 return nullptr;
2395
2396 // If the add does not wrap, we can always adjust the compare by subtracting
2397 // the constants. Equality comparisons are handled elsewhere. SGE/SLE/UGE/ULE
2398 // are canonicalized to SGT/SLT/UGT/ULT.
2399 if ((Add->hasNoSignedWrap() &&
2400 (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT)) ||
2401 (Add->hasNoUnsignedWrap() &&
2402 (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT))) {
2403 bool Overflow;
2404 APInt NewC =
2405 Cmp.isSigned() ? C.ssub_ov(*C2, Overflow) : C.usub_ov(*C2, Overflow);
2406 // If there is overflow, the result must be true or false.
2407 // TODO: Can we assert there is no overflow because InstSimplify always
2408 // handles those cases?
2409 if (!Overflow)
2410 // icmp Pred (add nsw X, C2), C --> icmp Pred X, (C - C2)
2411 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, NewC));
2412 }
2413
2414 auto CR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(Pred, C).subtract(*C2);
2415 const APInt &Upper = CR.getUpper();
2416 const APInt &Lower = CR.getLower();
2417 if (Cmp.isSigned()) {
2418 if (Lower.isSignMask())
2419 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Upper));
2420 if (Upper.isSignMask())
2421 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Lower));
2422 } else {
2423 if (Lower.isMinValue())
2424 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Upper));
2425 if (Upper.isMinValue())
2426 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, X, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Lower));
2427 }
2428
2429 // X+C <u C2 -> (X & -C2) == C
2430 // iff C & (C2-1) == 0
2431 // C2 is a power of 2
2432 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && C.isPowerOf2() && (*C2 & (C - 1)) == 0)
2433 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Builder.CreateAnd(X, -C),
2434 ConstantExpr::getNeg(cast<Constant>(Y)));
2435
2436 // X+C >u C2 -> (X & ~C2) != C
2437 // iff C & C2 == 0
2438 // C2+1 is a power of 2
2439 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && (C + 1).isPowerOf2() && (*C2 & C) == 0)
2440 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Builder.CreateAnd(X, ~C),
2441 ConstantExpr::getNeg(cast<Constant>(Y)));
2442
2443 return nullptr;
2444}
2445
2446bool InstCombiner::matchThreeWayIntCompare(SelectInst *SI, Value *&LHS,
2447 Value *&RHS, ConstantInt *&Less,
2448 ConstantInt *&Equal,
2449 ConstantInt *&Greater) {
2450 // TODO: Generalize this to work with other comparison idioms or ensure
2451 // they get canonicalized into this form.
2452
2453 // select i1 (a == b), i32 Equal, i32 (select i1 (a < b), i32 Less, i32
2454 // Greater), where Equal, Less and Greater are placeholders for any three
2455 // constants.
2456 ICmpInst::Predicate PredA, PredB;
2457 if (match(SI->getTrueValue(), m_ConstantInt(Equal)) &&
2458 match(SI->getCondition(), m_ICmp(PredA, m_Value(LHS), m_Value(RHS))) &&
2459 PredA == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ &&
2460 match(SI->getFalseValue(),
2461 m_Select(m_ICmp(PredB, m_Specific(LHS), m_Specific(RHS)),
2462 m_ConstantInt(Less), m_ConstantInt(Greater))) &&
2463 PredB == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT) {
2464 return true;
2465 }
2466 return false;
2467}
2468
2469Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpSelectConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2470 SelectInst *Select,
2471 ConstantInt *C) {
2472
2473 assert(C && "Cmp RHS should be a constant int!");
2474 // If we're testing a constant value against the result of a three way
2475 // comparison, the result can be expressed directly in terms of the
2476 // original values being compared. Note: We could possibly be more
2477 // aggressive here and remove the hasOneUse test. The original select is
2478 // really likely to simplify or sink when we remove a test of the result.
2479 Value *OrigLHS, *OrigRHS;
2480 ConstantInt *C1LessThan, *C2Equal, *C3GreaterThan;
2481 if (Cmp.hasOneUse() &&
2482 matchThreeWayIntCompare(Select, OrigLHS, OrigRHS, C1LessThan, C2Equal,
2483 C3GreaterThan)) {
2484 assert(C1LessThan && C2Equal && C3GreaterThan);
2485
2486 bool TrueWhenLessThan =
2487 ConstantExpr::getCompare(Cmp.getPredicate(), C1LessThan, C)
2488 ->isAllOnesValue();
2489 bool TrueWhenEqual =
2490 ConstantExpr::getCompare(Cmp.getPredicate(), C2Equal, C)
2491 ->isAllOnesValue();
2492 bool TrueWhenGreaterThan =
2493 ConstantExpr::getCompare(Cmp.getPredicate(), C3GreaterThan, C)
2494 ->isAllOnesValue();
2495
2496 // This generates the new instruction that will replace the original Cmp
2497 // Instruction. Instead of enumerating the various combinations when
2498 // TrueWhenLessThan, TrueWhenEqual and TrueWhenGreaterThan are true versus
2499 // false, we rely on chaining of ORs and future passes of InstCombine to
2500 // simplify the OR further (i.e. a s< b || a == b becomes a s<= b).
2501
2502 // When none of the three constants satisfy the predicate for the RHS (C),
2503 // the entire original Cmp can be simplified to a false.
2504 Value *Cond = Builder.getFalse();
2505 if (TrueWhenLessThan)
2506 Cond = Builder.CreateOr(Cond, Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT,
2507 OrigLHS, OrigRHS));
2508 if (TrueWhenEqual)
2509 Cond = Builder.CreateOr(Cond, Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ,
2510 OrigLHS, OrigRHS));
2511 if (TrueWhenGreaterThan)
2512 Cond = Builder.CreateOr(Cond, Builder.CreateICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT,
2513 OrigLHS, OrigRHS));
2514
2515 return replaceInstUsesWith(Cmp, Cond);
2516 }
2517 return nullptr;
2518}
2519
2520static Instruction *foldICmpBitCast(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2521 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
2522 auto *Bitcast = dyn_cast<BitCastInst>(Cmp.getOperand(0));
2523 if (!Bitcast)
2524 return nullptr;
2525
2526 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2527 Value *Op1 = Cmp.getOperand(1);
2528 Value *BCSrcOp = Bitcast->getOperand(0);
2529
2530 // Make sure the bitcast doesn't change the number of vector elements.
2531 if (Bitcast->getSrcTy()->getScalarSizeInBits() ==
2532 Bitcast->getDestTy()->getScalarSizeInBits()) {
2533 // Zero-equality and sign-bit checks are preserved through sitofp + bitcast.
2534 Value *X;
2535 if (match(BCSrcOp, m_SIToFP(m_Value(X)))) {
2536 // icmp eq (bitcast (sitofp X)), 0 --> icmp eq X, 0
2537 // icmp ne (bitcast (sitofp X)), 0 --> icmp ne X, 0
2538 // icmp slt (bitcast (sitofp X)), 0 --> icmp slt X, 0
2539 // icmp sgt (bitcast (sitofp X)), 0 --> icmp sgt X, 0
2540 if ((Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT ||
2541 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT) &&
2542 match(Op1, m_Zero()))
2543 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::getNullValue(X->getType()));
2544
2545 // icmp slt (bitcast (sitofp X)), 1 --> icmp slt X, 1
2546 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(Op1, m_One()))
2547 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::get(X->getType(), 1));
2548
2549 // icmp sgt (bitcast (sitofp X)), -1 --> icmp sgt X, -1
2550 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(Op1, m_AllOnes()))
2551 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X,
2552 ConstantInt::getAllOnesValue(X->getType()));
2553 }
2554
2555 // Zero-equality checks are preserved through unsigned floating-point casts:
2556 // icmp eq (bitcast (uitofp X)), 0 --> icmp eq X, 0
2557 // icmp ne (bitcast (uitofp X)), 0 --> icmp ne X, 0
2558 if (match(BCSrcOp, m_UIToFP(m_Value(X))))
2559 if (Cmp.isEquality() && match(Op1, m_Zero()))
2560 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, ConstantInt::getNullValue(X->getType()));
2561 }
2562
2563 // Test to see if the operands of the icmp are casted versions of other
2564 // values. If the ptr->ptr cast can be stripped off both arguments, do so.
2565 if (Bitcast->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
2566 (isa<Constant>(Op1) || isa<BitCastInst>(Op1))) {
2567 // If operand #1 is a bitcast instruction, it must also be a ptr->ptr cast
2568 // so eliminate it as well.
2569 if (auto *BC2 = dyn_cast<BitCastInst>(Op1))
2570 Op1 = BC2->getOperand(0);
2571
2572 Op1 = Builder.CreateBitCast(Op1, BCSrcOp->getType());
2573 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BCSrcOp, Op1);
2574 }
2575
2576 // Folding: icmp <pred> iN X, C
2577 // where X = bitcast <M x iK> (shufflevector <M x iK> %vec, undef, SC)) to iN
2578 // and C is a splat of a K-bit pattern
2579 // and SC is a constant vector = <C', C', C', ..., C'>
2580 // Into:
2581 // %E = extractelement <M x iK> %vec, i32 C'
2582 // icmp <pred> iK %E, trunc(C)
2583 const APInt *C;
2584 if (!match(Cmp.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) ||
2585 !Bitcast->getType()->isIntegerTy() ||
2586 !Bitcast->getSrcTy()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
2587 return nullptr;
2588
2589 Value *Vec;
2590 Constant *Mask;
2591 if (match(BCSrcOp,
2592 m_ShuffleVector(m_Value(Vec), m_Undef(), m_Constant(Mask)))) {
2593 // Check whether every element of Mask is the same constant
2594 if (auto *Elem = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(Mask->getSplatValue())) {
2595 auto *VecTy = cast<VectorType>(BCSrcOp->getType());
2596 auto *EltTy = cast<IntegerType>(VecTy->getElementType());
2597 if (C->isSplat(EltTy->getBitWidth())) {
2598 // Fold the icmp based on the value of C
2599 // If C is M copies of an iK sized bit pattern,
2600 // then:
2601 // => %E = extractelement <N x iK> %vec, i32 Elem
2602 // icmp <pred> iK %SplatVal, <pattern>
2603 Value *Extract = Builder.CreateExtractElement(Vec, Elem);
2604 Value *NewC = ConstantInt::get(EltTy, C->trunc(EltTy->getBitWidth()));
2605 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Extract, NewC);
2606 }
2607 }
2608 }
2609 return nullptr;
2610}
2611
2612/// Try to fold integer comparisons with a constant operand: icmp Pred X, C
2613/// where X is some kind of instruction.
2614Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpInstWithConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp) {
2615 const APInt *C;
2616 if (!match(Cmp.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
2617 return nullptr;
2618
2619 if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Cmp.getOperand(0))) {
2620 switch (BO->getOpcode()) {
2621 case Instruction::Xor:
2622 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpXorConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2623 return I;
2624 break;
2625 case Instruction::And:
2626 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpAndConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2627 return I;
2628 break;
2629 case Instruction::Or:
2630 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpOrConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2631 return I;
2632 break;
2633 case Instruction::Mul:
2634 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpMulConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2635 return I;
2636 break;
2637 case Instruction::Shl:
2638 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpShlConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2639 return I;
2640 break;
2641 case Instruction::LShr:
2642 case Instruction::AShr:
2643 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpShrConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2644 return I;
2645 break;
2646 case Instruction::UDiv:
2647 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpUDivConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2648 return I;
2649 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2650 case Instruction::SDiv:
2651 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpDivConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2652 return I;
2653 break;
2654 case Instruction::Sub:
2655 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpSubConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2656 return I;
2657 break;
2658 case Instruction::Add:
2659 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpAddConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2660 return I;
2661 break;
2662 default:
2663 break;
2664 }
2665 // TODO: These folds could be refactored to be part of the above calls.
2666 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant(Cmp, BO, *C))
2667 return I;
2668 }
2669
2670 // Match against CmpInst LHS being instructions other than binary operators.
2671
2672 if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(Cmp.getOperand(0))) {
2673 // For now, we only support constant integers while folding the
2674 // ICMP(SELECT)) pattern. We can extend this to support vector of integers
2675 // similar to the cases handled by binary ops above.
2676 if (ConstantInt *ConstRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Cmp.getOperand(1)))
2677 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpSelectConstant(Cmp, SI, ConstRHS))
2678 return I;
2679 }
2680
2681 if (auto *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(Cmp.getOperand(0))) {
2682 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpTruncConstant(Cmp, TI, *C))
2683 return I;
2684 }
2685
2686 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Cmp.getOperand(0)))
2687 if (Instruction *I = foldICmpIntrinsicWithConstant(Cmp, II, *C))
2688 return I;
2689
2690 return nullptr;
2691}
2692
2693/// Fold an icmp equality instruction with binary operator LHS and constant RHS:
2694/// icmp eq/ne BO, C.
2695Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpBinOpEqualityWithConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2696 BinaryOperator *BO,
2697 const APInt &C) {
2698 // TODO: Some of these folds could work with arbitrary constants, but this
2699 // function is limited to scalar and vector splat constants.
2700 if (!Cmp.isEquality())
2701 return nullptr;
2702
2703 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
2704 bool isICMP_NE = Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
2705 Constant *RHS = cast<Constant>(Cmp.getOperand(1));
2706 Value *BOp0 = BO->getOperand(0), *BOp1 = BO->getOperand(1);
2707
2708 switch (BO->getOpcode()) {
2709 case Instruction::SRem:
2710 // If we have a signed (X % (2^c)) == 0, turn it into an unsigned one.
2711 if (C.isNullValue() && BO->hasOneUse()) {
2712 const APInt *BOC;
2713 if (match(BOp1, m_APInt(BOC)) && BOC->sgt(1) && BOC->isPowerOf2()) {
2714 Value *NewRem = Builder.CreateURem(BOp0, BOp1, BO->getName());
2715 return new ICmpInst(Pred, NewRem,
2716 Constant::getNullValue(BO->getType()));
2717 }
2718 }
2719 break;
2720 case Instruction::Add: {
2721 // Replace ((add A, B) != C) with (A != C-B) if B & C are constants.
2722 const APInt *BOC;
2723 if (match(BOp1, m_APInt(BOC))) {
2724 if (BO->hasOneUse()) {
2725 Constant *SubC = ConstantExpr::getSub(RHS, cast<Constant>(BOp1));
2726 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, SubC);
2727 }
2728 } else if (C.isNullValue()) {
2729 // Replace ((add A, B) != 0) with (A != -B) if A or B is
2730 // efficiently invertible, or if the add has just this one use.
2731 if (Value *NegVal = dyn_castNegVal(BOp1))
2732 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, NegVal);
2733 if (Value *NegVal = dyn_castNegVal(BOp0))
2734 return new ICmpInst(Pred, NegVal, BOp1);
2735 if (BO->hasOneUse()) {
2736 Value *Neg = Builder.CreateNeg(BOp1);
2737 Neg->takeName(BO);
2738 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, Neg);
2739 }
2740 }
2741 break;
2742 }
2743 case Instruction::Xor:
2744 if (BO->hasOneUse()) {
2745 if (Constant *BOC = dyn_cast<Constant>(BOp1)) {
2746 // For the xor case, we can xor two constants together, eliminating
2747 // the explicit xor.
2748 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, ConstantExpr::getXor(RHS, BOC));
2749 } else if (C.isNullValue()) {
2750 // Replace ((xor A, B) != 0) with (A != B)
2751 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, BOp1);
2752 }
2753 }
2754 break;
2755 case Instruction::Sub:
2756 if (BO->hasOneUse()) {
2757 const APInt *BOC;
2758 if (match(BOp0, m_APInt(BOC))) {
2759 // Replace ((sub BOC, B) != C) with (B != BOC-C).
2760 Constant *SubC = ConstantExpr::getSub(cast<Constant>(BOp0), RHS);
2761 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp1, SubC);
2762 } else if (C.isNullValue()) {
2763 // Replace ((sub A, B) != 0) with (A != B).
2764 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, BOp1);
2765 }
2766 }
2767 break;
2768 case Instruction::Or: {
2769 const APInt *BOC;
2770 if (match(BOp1, m_APInt(BOC)) && BO->hasOneUse() && RHS->isAllOnesValue()) {
2771 // Comparing if all bits outside of a constant mask are set?
2772 // Replace (X | C) == -1 with (X & ~C) == ~C.
2773 // This removes the -1 constant.
2774 Constant *NotBOC = ConstantExpr::getNot(cast<Constant>(BOp1));
2775 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(BOp0, NotBOC);
2776 return new ICmpInst(Pred, And, NotBOC);
2777 }
2778 break;
2779 }
2780 case Instruction::And: {
2781 const APInt *BOC;
2782 if (match(BOp1, m_APInt(BOC))) {
2783 // If we have ((X & C) == C), turn it into ((X & C) != 0).
2784 if (C == *BOC && C.isPowerOf2())
2785 return new ICmpInst(isICMP_NE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ : ICmpInst::ICMP_NE,
2786 BO, Constant::getNullValue(RHS->getType()));
2787
2788 // Don't perform the following transforms if the AND has multiple uses
2789 if (!BO->hasOneUse())
2790 break;
2791
2792 // Replace (and X, (1 << size(X)-1) != 0) with x s< 0
2793 if (BOC->isSignMask()) {
2794 Constant *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(BOp0->getType());
2795 auto NewPred = isICMP_NE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT : ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE;
2796 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, BOp0, Zero);
2797 }
2798
2799 // ((X & ~7) == 0) --> X < 8
2800 if (C.isNullValue() && (~(*BOC) + 1).isPowerOf2()) {
2801 Constant *NegBOC = ConstantExpr::getNeg(cast<Constant>(BOp1));
2802 auto NewPred = isICMP_NE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
2803 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, BOp0, NegBOC);
2804 }
2805 }
2806 break;
2807 }
2808 case Instruction::Mul:
2809 if (C.isNullValue() && BO->hasNoSignedWrap()) {
2810 const APInt *BOC;
2811 if (match(BOp1, m_APInt(BOC)) && !BOC->isNullValue()) {
2812 // The trivial case (mul X, 0) is handled by InstSimplify.
2813 // General case : (mul X, C) != 0 iff X != 0
2814 // (mul X, C) == 0 iff X == 0
2815 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BOp0, Constant::getNullValue(RHS->getType()));
2816 }
2817 }
2818 break;
2819 case Instruction::UDiv:
2820 if (C.isNullValue()) {
2821 // (icmp eq/ne (udiv A, B), 0) -> (icmp ugt/ule i32 B, A)
2822 auto NewPred = isICMP_NE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE : ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
2823 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, BOp1, BOp0);
2824 }
2825 break;
2826 default:
2827 break;
2828 }
2829 return nullptr;
2830}

2832/// Fold an equality icmp with LLVM intrinsic and constant operand.
2833Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpEqIntrinsicWithConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2834 IntrinsicInst *II,
2835 const APInt &C) {
2836 Type *Ty = II->getType();
2837 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth();
2838 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
2839 case Intrinsic::bswap:
2840 Worklist.Add(II);
2841 Cmp.setOperand(0, II->getArgOperand(0));
2842 Cmp.setOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(Ty, C.byteSwap()));
2843 return &Cmp;
2844
2845 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
2846 case Intrinsic::cttz: {
2847 // ctz(A) == bitwidth(A) -> A == 0 and likewise for !=
2848 if (C == BitWidth) {
2849 Worklist.Add(II);
2850 Cmp.setOperand(0, II->getArgOperand(0));
2851 Cmp.setOperand(1, ConstantInt::getNullValue(Ty));
2852 return &Cmp;
2853 }
2854
2855 // ctz(A) == C -> A & Mask1 == Mask2, where Mask2 only has bit C set
2856 // and Mask1 has bits 0..C+1 set. Similar for ctl, but for high bits.
2857 // Limit to one use to ensure we don't increase instruction count.
2858 unsigned Num = C.getLimitedValue(BitWidth);
2859 if (Num != BitWidth && II->hasOneUse()) {
2860 bool IsTrailing = II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::cttz;
2861 APInt Mask1 = IsTrailing ? APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, Num + 1)
2862 : APInt::getHighBitsSet(BitWidth, Num + 1);
2863 APInt Mask2 = IsTrailing
2864 ? APInt::getOneBitSet(BitWidth, Num)
2865 : APInt::getOneBitSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - Num - 1);
2866 Cmp.setOperand(0, Builder.CreateAnd(II->getArgOperand(0), Mask1));
2867 Cmp.setOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Mask2));
2868 Worklist.Add(II);
2869 return &Cmp;
2870 }
2871 break;
2872 }
2873
2874 case Intrinsic::ctpop: {
2875 // popcount(A) == 0 -> A == 0 and likewise for !=
2876 // popcount(A) == bitwidth(A) -> A == -1 and likewise for !=
2877 bool IsZero = C.isNullValue();
2878 if (IsZero || C == BitWidth) {
2879 Worklist.Add(II);
2880 Cmp.setOperand(0, II->getArgOperand(0));
2881 auto *NewOp =
2882 IsZero ? Constant::getNullValue(Ty) : Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty);
2883 Cmp.setOperand(1, NewOp);
2884 return &Cmp;
2885 }
2886 break;
2887 }
2888 default:
2889 break;
2890 }
2891
2892 return nullptr;
2893}
2894
2895/// Fold an icmp with LLVM intrinsic and constant operand: icmp Pred II, C.
2896Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpIntrinsicWithConstant(ICmpInst &Cmp,
2897 IntrinsicInst *II,
2898 const APInt &C) {
2899 if (Cmp.isEquality())
2900 return foldICmpEqIntrinsicWithConstant(Cmp, II, C);
2901
2902 Type *Ty = II->getType();
2903 unsigned BitWidth = C.getBitWidth();
2904 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
2905 case Intrinsic::ctlz: {
2906 // ctlz(0bXXXXXXXX) > 3 -> 0bXXXXXXXX < 0b00010000
2907 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && C.ult(BitWidth)) {
2908 unsigned Num = C.getLimitedValue();
2909 APInt Limit = APInt::getOneBitSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - Num - 1);
2910 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT,
2911 II->getArgOperand(0), ConstantInt::get(Ty, Limit));
2912 }
2913
2914 // ctlz(0bXXXXXXXX) < 3 -> 0bXXXXXXXX > 0b00011111
2915 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT &&
2916 C.uge(1) && C.ule(BitWidth)) {
2917 unsigned Num = C.getLimitedValue();
2918 APInt Limit = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, BitWidth - Num);
2919 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT,
2920 II->getArgOperand(0), ConstantInt::get(Ty, Limit));
2921 }
2922 break;
2923 }
2924 case Intrinsic::cttz: {
2925 // Limit to one use to ensure we don't increase instruction count.
2926 if (!II->hasOneUse())
2927 return nullptr;
2928
2929 // cttz(0bXXXXXXXX) > 3 -> 0bXXXXXXXX & 0b00001111 == 0
2930 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && C.ult(BitWidth)) {
2931 APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, C.getLimitedValue() + 1);
2932 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ,
2933 Builder.CreateAnd(II->getArgOperand(0), Mask),
2934 ConstantInt::getNullValue(Ty));
2935 }
2936
2937 // cttz(0bXXXXXXXX) < 3 -> 0bXXXXXXXX & 0b00000111 != 0
2938 if (Cmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT &&
2939 C.uge(1) && C.ule(BitWidth)) {
2940 APInt Mask = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, C.getLimitedValue());
2941 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, ICmpInst::ICMP_NE,
2942 Builder.CreateAnd(II->getArgOperand(0), Mask),
2943 ConstantInt::getNullValue(Ty));
2944 }
2945 break;
2946 }
2947 default:
2948 break;
2949 }
2950
2951 return nullptr;
2952}

2954/// Handle icmp with constant (but not simple integer constant) RHS.
2955Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpInstWithConstantNotInt(ICmpInst &I) {
2956 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
2957 Constant *RHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op1);
2958 Instruction *LHSI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Op0);
2959 if (!RHSC || !LHSI)
2960 return nullptr;
2961
2962 switch (LHSI->getOpcode()) {
2963 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
2964 // icmp pred GEP (P, int 0, int 0, int 0), null -> icmp pred P, null
2965 if (RHSC->isNullValue() &&
2966 cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LHSI)->hasAllZeroIndices())
2967 return new ICmpInst(
2968 I.getPredicate(), LHSI->getOperand(0),
2969 Constant::getNullValue(LHSI->getOperand(0)->getType()));
2970 break;
2971 case Instruction::PHI:
2972 // Only fold icmp into the PHI if the phi and icmp are in the same
2973 // block. If in the same block, we're encouraging jump threading. If
2974 // not, we are just pessimizing the code by making an i1 phi.
2975 if (LHSI->getParent() == I.getParent())
2976 if (Instruction *NV = foldOpIntoPhi(I, cast<PHINode>(LHSI)))
2977 return NV;
2978 break;
2979 case Instruction::Select: {
2980 // If either operand of the select is a constant, we can fold the
2981 // comparison into the select arms, which will cause one to be
2982 // constant folded and the select turned into a bitwise or.
2983 Value *Op1 = nullptr, *Op2 = nullptr;
2984 ConstantInt *CI = nullptr;
2985 if (Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(LHSI->getOperand(1))) {
2986 Op1 = ConstantExpr::getICmp(I.getPredicate(), C, RHSC);
2987 CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op1);
2988 }
2989 if (Constant *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(LHSI->getOperand(2))) {
2990 Op2 = ConstantExpr::getICmp(I.getPredicate(), C, RHSC);
2991 CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op2);
2992 }
2993
2994 // We only want to perform this transformation if it will not lead to
2995 // additional code. This is true if either both sides of the select
2996 // fold to a constant (in which case the icmp is replaced with a select
2997 // which will usually simplify) or this is the only user of the
2998 // select (in which case we are trading a select+icmp for a simpler
2999 // select+icmp) or all uses of the select can be replaced based on
3000 // dominance information ("Global cases").
3001 bool Transform = false;
3002 if (Op1 && Op2)
3003 Transform = true;
3004 else if (Op1 || Op2) {
3005 // Local case
3006 if (LHSI->hasOneUse())
3007 Transform = true;
3008 // Global cases
3009 else if (CI && !CI->isZero())
3010 // When Op1 is constant try replacing select with second operand.
3011 // Otherwise Op2 is constant and try replacing select with first
3012 // operand.
3013 Transform =
3014 replacedSelectWithOperand(cast<SelectInst>(LHSI), &I, Op1 ? 2 : 1);
3015 }
3016 if (Transform) {
3017 if (!Op1)
3018 Op1 = Builder.CreateICmp(I.getPredicate(), LHSI->getOperand(1), RHSC,
3019 I.getName());
3020 if (!Op2)
3021 Op2 = Builder.CreateICmp(I.getPredicate(), LHSI->getOperand(2), RHSC,
3022 I.getName());
3023 return SelectInst::Create(LHSI->getOperand(0), Op1, Op2);
3024 }
3025 break;
3026 }
3027 case Instruction::IntToPtr:
3028 // icmp pred inttoptr(X), null -> icmp pred X, 0
3029 if (RHSC->isNullValue() &&
3030 DL.getIntPtrType(RHSC->getType()) == LHSI->getOperand(0)->getType())
3031 return new ICmpInst(
3032 I.getPredicate(), LHSI->getOperand(0),
3033 Constant::getNullValue(LHSI->getOperand(0)->getType()));
3034 break;
3035
3036 case Instruction::Load:
3037 // Try to optimize things like "A[i] > 4" to index computations.
3038 if (GetElementPtrInst *GEP =
3039 dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LHSI->getOperand(0))) {
3040 if (GlobalVariable *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GEP->getOperand(0)))
3041 if (GV->isConstant() && GV->hasDefinitiveInitializer() &&
3042 !cast<LoadInst>(LHSI)->isVolatile())
3043 if (Instruction *Res = foldCmpLoadFromIndexedGlobal(GEP, GV, I))
3044 return Res;
3045 }
3046 break;
3047 }
3048
3049 return nullptr;
3050}
