3052/// Some comparisons can be simplified.
3053/// In this case, we are looking for comparisons that look like
3054/// a check for a lossy truncation.
3055/// Folds:
3056/// icmp SrcPred (x & Mask), x to icmp DstPred x, Mask
3057/// Where Mask is some pattern that produces all-ones in low bits:
3058/// (-1 >> y)
3059/// ((-1 << y) >> y) <- non-canonical, has extra uses
3060/// ~(-1 << y)
3061/// ((1 << y) + (-1)) <- non-canonical, has extra uses
3062/// The Mask can be a constant, too.
3063/// For some predicates, the operands are commutative.
3064/// For others, x can only be on a specific side.
3065static Value *foldICmpWithLowBitMaskedVal(ICmpInst &I,
3066 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
3067 ICmpInst::Predicate SrcPred;
3068 Value *X, *M, *Y;
3069 auto m_VariableMask = m_CombineOr(
3070 m_CombineOr(m_Not(m_Shl(m_AllOnes(), m_Value())),
3071 m_Add(m_Shl(m_One(), m_Value()), m_AllOnes())),
3072 m_CombineOr(m_LShr(m_AllOnes(), m_Value()),
3073 m_LShr(m_Shl(m_AllOnes(), m_Value(Y)), m_Deferred(Y))));
3074 auto m_Mask = m_CombineOr(m_VariableMask, m_LowBitMask());
3075 if (!match(&I, m_c_ICmp(SrcPred,
3076 m_c_And(m_CombineAnd(m_Mask, m_Value(M)), m_Value(X)),
3077 m_Deferred(X))))
3078 return nullptr;
3079
3080 ICmpInst::Predicate DstPred;
3081 switch (SrcPred) {
3082 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ:
3083 // x & (-1 >> y) == x -> x u<= (-1 >> y)
3084 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULE;
3085 break;
3086 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_NE:
3087 // x & (-1 >> y) != x -> x u> (-1 >> y)
3088 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGT;
3089 break;
3090 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGT:
3091 // x u> x & (-1 >> y) -> x u> (-1 >> y)
3092 assert(X == I.getOperand(0) && "instsimplify took care of commut. variant");
3093 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGT;
3094 break;
3095 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGE:
3096 // x & (-1 >> y) u>= x -> x u<= (-1 >> y)
3097 assert(X == I.getOperand(1) && "instsimplify took care of commut. variant");
3098 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULE;
3099 break;
3100 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULT:
3101 // x & (-1 >> y) u< x -> x u> (-1 >> y)
3102 assert(X == I.getOperand(1) && "instsimplify took care of commut. variant");
3103 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGT;
3104 break;
3105 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULE:
3106 // x u<= x & (-1 >> y) -> x u<= (-1 >> y)
3107 assert(X == I.getOperand(0) && "instsimplify took care of commut. variant");
3108 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULE;
3109 break;
3110 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SGT:
3111 // x s> x & (-1 >> y) -> x s> (-1 >> y)
3112 if (X != I.getOperand(0)) // X must be on LHS of comparison!
3113 return nullptr; // Ignore the other case.
3114 if (!match(M, m_Constant())) // Can not do this fold with non-constant.
3115 return nullptr;
3116 if (!match(M, m_NonNegative())) // Must not have any -1 vector elements.
3117 return nullptr;
3118 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SGT;
3119 break;
3120 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SGE:
3121 // x & (-1 >> y) s>= x -> x s<= (-1 >> y)
3122 if (X != I.getOperand(1)) // X must be on RHS of comparison!
3123 return nullptr; // Ignore the other case.
3124 if (!match(M, m_Constant())) // Can not do this fold with non-constant.
3125 return nullptr;
3126 if (!match(M, m_NonNegative())) // Must not have any -1 vector elements.
3127 return nullptr;
3128 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SLE;
3129 break;
3130 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SLT:
3131 // x & (-1 >> y) s< x -> x s> (-1 >> y)
3132 if (X != I.getOperand(1)) // X must be on RHS of comparison!
3133 return nullptr; // Ignore the other case.
3134 if (!match(M, m_Constant())) // Can not do this fold with non-constant.
3135 return nullptr;
3136 if (!match(M, m_NonNegative())) // Must not have any -1 vector elements.
3137 return nullptr;
3138 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SGT;
3139 break;
3140 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SLE:
3141 // x s<= x & (-1 >> y) -> x s<= (-1 >> y)
3142 if (X != I.getOperand(0)) // X must be on LHS of comparison!
3143 return nullptr; // Ignore the other case.
3144 if (!match(M, m_Constant())) // Can not do this fold with non-constant.
3145 return nullptr;
3146 if (!match(M, m_NonNegative())) // Must not have any -1 vector elements.
3147 return nullptr;
3148 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_SLE;
3149 break;
3150 default:
3151 llvm_unreachable("All possible folds are handled.");
3152 }
3153
3154 return Builder.CreateICmp(DstPred, X, M);
3155}
3156
3157/// Some comparisons can be simplified.
3158/// In this case, we are looking for comparisons that look like
3159/// a check for a lossy signed truncation.
3160/// Folds: (MaskedBits is a constant.)
3161/// ((%x << MaskedBits) a>> MaskedBits) SrcPred %x
3162/// Into:
3163/// (add %x, (1 << (KeptBits-1))) DstPred (1 << KeptBits)
3164/// Where KeptBits = bitwidth(%x) - MaskedBits
3165static Value *
3166foldICmpWithTruncSignExtendedVal(ICmpInst &I,
3167 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
3168 ICmpInst::Predicate SrcPred;
3169 Value *X;
3170 const APInt *C0, *C1; // FIXME: non-splats, potentially with undef.
3171 // We are ok with 'shl' having multiple uses, but 'ashr' must be one-use.
3172 if (!match(&I, m_c_ICmp(SrcPred,
3173 m_OneUse(m_AShr(m_Shl(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0)),
3174 m_APInt(C1))),
3175 m_Deferred(X))))
3176 return nullptr;
3177
3178 // Potential handling of non-splats: for each element:
3179 // * if both are undef, replace with constant 0.
3180 // Because (1<<0) is OK and is 1, and ((1<<0)>>1) is also OK and is 0.
3181 // * if both are not undef, and are different, bailout.
3182 // * else, only one is undef, then pick the non-undef one.
3183
3184 // The shift amount must be equal.
3185 if (*C0 != *C1)
3186 return nullptr;
3187 const APInt &MaskedBits = *C0;
3188 assert(MaskedBits != 0 && "shift by zero should be folded away already.");
3189
3190 ICmpInst::Predicate DstPred;
3191 switch (SrcPred) {
3192 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_EQ:
3193 // ((%x << MaskedBits) a>> MaskedBits) == %x
3194 // =>
3195 // (add %x, (1 << (KeptBits-1))) u< (1 << KeptBits)
3196 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_ULT;
3197 break;
3198 case ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_NE:
3199 // ((%x << MaskedBits) a>> MaskedBits) != %x
3200 // =>
3201 // (add %x, (1 << (KeptBits-1))) u>= (1 << KeptBits)
3202 DstPred = ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_UGE;
3203 break;
3204 // FIXME: are more folds possible?
3205 default:
3206 return nullptr;
3207 }
3208
3209 auto *XType = X->getType();
3210 const unsigned XBitWidth = XType->getScalarSizeInBits();
3211 const APInt BitWidth = APInt(XBitWidth, XBitWidth);
3212 assert(BitWidth.ugt(MaskedBits) && "shifts should leave some bits untouched");
3213
3214 // KeptBits = bitwidth(%x) - MaskedBits
3215 const APInt KeptBits = BitWidth - MaskedBits;
3216 assert(KeptBits.ugt(0) && KeptBits.ult(BitWidth) && "unreachable");
3217 // ICmpCst = (1 << KeptBits)
3218 const APInt ICmpCst = APInt(XBitWidth, 1).shl(KeptBits);
3219 assert(ICmpCst.isPowerOf2());
3220 // AddCst = (1 << (KeptBits-1))
3221 const APInt AddCst = ICmpCst.lshr(1);
3222 assert(AddCst.ult(ICmpCst) && AddCst.isPowerOf2());
3223
3224 // T0 = add %x, AddCst
3225 Value *T0 = Builder.CreateAdd(X, ConstantInt::get(XType, AddCst));
3226 // T1 = T0 DstPred ICmpCst
3227 Value *T1 = Builder.CreateICmp(DstPred, T0, ConstantInt::get(XType, ICmpCst));
3228
3229 return T1;
3230}
3231
3232/// Try to fold icmp (binop), X or icmp X, (binop).
3233/// TODO: A large part of this logic is duplicated in InstSimplify's
3234/// simplifyICmpWithBinOp(). We should be able to share that and avoid the code
3235/// duplication.
3236Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpBinOp(ICmpInst &I) {
3237 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
3238
3239 // Special logic for binary operators.
3240 BinaryOperator *BO0 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op0);
3241 BinaryOperator *BO1 = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(Op1);
3242 if (!BO0 && !BO1)
3243 return nullptr;
3244
3245 const CmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
3246 Value *X;
3247
3248 // Convert add-with-unsigned-overflow comparisons into a 'not' with compare.
3249 // (Op1 + X) <u Op1 --> ~Op1 <u X
3250 // Op0 >u (Op0 + X) --> X >u ~Op0
3251 if (match(Op0, m_OneUse(m_c_Add(m_Specific(Op1), m_Value(X)))) &&
3252 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
3253 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Builder.CreateNot(Op1), X);
3254 if (match(Op1, m_OneUse(m_c_Add(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value(X)))) &&
3255 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
3256 return new ICmpInst(Pred, X, Builder.CreateNot(Op0));
3257
3258 bool NoOp0WrapProblem = false, NoOp1WrapProblem = false;
3259 if (BO0 && isa<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(BO0))
3260 NoOp0WrapProblem =
3261 ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) ||
3262 (CmpInst::isUnsigned(Pred) && BO0->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) ||
3263 (CmpInst::isSigned(Pred) && BO0->hasNoSignedWrap());
3264 if (BO1 && isa<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(BO1))
3265 NoOp1WrapProblem =
3266 ICmpInst::isEquality(Pred) ||
3267 (CmpInst::isUnsigned(Pred) && BO1->hasNoUnsignedWrap()) ||
3268 (CmpInst::isSigned(Pred) && BO1->hasNoSignedWrap());
3269
3270 // Analyze the case when either Op0 or Op1 is an add instruction.
3271 // Op0 = A + B (or A and B are null); Op1 = C + D (or C and D are null).
3272 Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr, *C = nullptr, *D = nullptr;
3273 if (BO0 && BO0->getOpcode() == Instruction::Add) {
3274 A = BO0->getOperand(0);
3275 B = BO0->getOperand(1);
3276 }
3277 if (BO1 && BO1->getOpcode() == Instruction::Add) {
3278 C = BO1->getOperand(0);
3279 D = BO1->getOperand(1);
3280 }
3281
3282 // icmp (X+Y), X -> icmp Y, 0 for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3283 if ((A == Op1 || B == Op1) && NoOp0WrapProblem)
3284 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A == Op1 ? B : A,
3285 Constant::getNullValue(Op1->getType()));
3286
3287 // icmp X, (X+Y) -> icmp 0, Y for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3288 if ((C == Op0 || D == Op0) && NoOp1WrapProblem)
3289 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType()),
3290 C == Op0 ? D : C);
3291
3292 // icmp (X+Y), (X+Z) -> icmp Y, Z for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3293 if (A && C && (A == C || A == D || B == C || B == D) && NoOp0WrapProblem &&
3294 NoOp1WrapProblem &&
3295 // Try not to increase register pressure.
3296 BO0->hasOneUse() && BO1->hasOneUse()) {
3297 // Determine Y and Z in the form icmp (X+Y), (X+Z).
3298 Value *Y, *Z;
3299 if (A == C) {
3300 // C + B == C + D -> B == D
3301 Y = B;
3302 Z = D;
3303 } else if (A == D) {
3304 // D + B == C + D -> B == C
3305 Y = B;
3306 Z = C;
3307 } else if (B == C) {
3308 // A + C == C + D -> A == D
3309 Y = A;
3310 Z = D;
3311 } else {
3312 assert(B == D);
3313 // A + D == C + D -> A == C
3314 Y = A;
3315 Z = C;
3316 }
3317 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Y, Z);
3318 }
3319
3320 // icmp slt (X + -1), Y -> icmp sle X, Y
3321 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT &&
3322 match(B, m_AllOnes()))
3323 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, A, Op1);
3324
3325 // icmp sge (X + -1), Y -> icmp sgt X, Y
3326 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGE &&
3327 match(B, m_AllOnes()))
3328 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SGT, A, Op1);
3329
3330 // icmp sle (X + 1), Y -> icmp slt X, Y
3331 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLE && match(B, m_One()))
3332 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SLT, A, Op1);
3333
3334 // icmp sgt (X + 1), Y -> icmp sge X, Y
3335 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(B, m_One()))
3336 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SGE, A, Op1);
3337
3338 // icmp sgt X, (Y + -1) -> icmp sge X, Y
3339 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT &&
3340 match(D, m_AllOnes()))
3341 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SGE, Op0, C);
3342
3343 // icmp sle X, (Y + -1) -> icmp slt X, Y
3344 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLE &&
3345 match(D, m_AllOnes()))
3346 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SLT, Op0, C);
3347
3348 // icmp sge X, (Y + 1) -> icmp sgt X, Y
3349 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGE && match(D, m_One()))
3350 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SGT, Op0, C);
3351
3352 // icmp slt X, (Y + 1) -> icmp sle X, Y
3353 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(D, m_One()))
3354 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, Op0, C);
3355
3356 // TODO: The subtraction-related identities shown below also hold, but
3357 // canonicalization from (X -nuw 1) to (X + -1) means that the combinations
3358 // wouldn't happen even if they were implemented.
3359 //
3360 // icmp ult (X - 1), Y -> icmp ule X, Y
3361 // icmp uge (X - 1), Y -> icmp ugt X, Y
3362 // icmp ugt X, (Y - 1) -> icmp uge X, Y
3363 // icmp ule X, (Y - 1) -> icmp ult X, Y
3364
3365 // icmp ule (X + 1), Y -> icmp ult X, Y
3366 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULE && match(B, m_One()))
3367 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_ULT, A, Op1);
3368
3369 // icmp ugt (X + 1), Y -> icmp uge X, Y
3370 if (A && NoOp0WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT && match(B, m_One()))
3371 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_UGE, A, Op1);
3372
3373 // icmp uge X, (Y + 1) -> icmp ugt X, Y
3374 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGE && match(D, m_One()))
3375 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_UGT, Op0, C);
3376
3377 // icmp ult X, (Y + 1) -> icmp ule X, Y
3378 if (C && NoOp1WrapProblem && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT && match(D, m_One()))
3379 return new ICmpInst(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, Op0, C);
3380
3381 // if C1 has greater magnitude than C2:
3382 // icmp (X + C1), (Y + C2) -> icmp (X + C3), Y
3383 // s.t. C3 = C1 - C2
3384 //
3385 // if C2 has greater magnitude than C1:
3386 // icmp (X + C1), (Y + C2) -> icmp X, (Y + C3)
3387 // s.t. C3 = C2 - C1
3388 if (A && C && NoOp0WrapProblem && NoOp1WrapProblem &&
3389 (BO0->hasOneUse() || BO1->hasOneUse()) && !I.isUnsigned())
3390 if (ConstantInt *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(B))
3391 if (ConstantInt *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(D)) {
3392 const APInt &AP1 = C1->getValue();
3393 const APInt &AP2 = C2->getValue();
3394 if (AP1.isNegative() == AP2.isNegative()) {
3395 APInt AP1Abs = C1->getValue().abs();
3396 APInt AP2Abs = C2->getValue().abs();
3397 if (AP1Abs.uge(AP2Abs)) {
3398 ConstantInt *C3 = Builder.getInt(AP1 - AP2);
3399 Value *NewAdd = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(A, C3);
3400 return new ICmpInst(Pred, NewAdd, C);
3401 } else {
3402 ConstantInt *C3 = Builder.getInt(AP2 - AP1);
3403 Value *NewAdd = Builder.CreateNSWAdd(C, C3);
3404 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, NewAdd);
3405 }
3406 }
3407 }
3408
3409 // Analyze the case when either Op0 or Op1 is a sub instruction.
3410 // Op0 = A - B (or A and B are null); Op1 = C - D (or C and D are null).
3411 A = nullptr;
3412 B = nullptr;
3413 C = nullptr;
3414 D = nullptr;
3415 if (BO0 && BO0->getOpcode() == Instruction::Sub) {
3416 A = BO0->getOperand(0);
3417 B = BO0->getOperand(1);
3418 }
3419 if (BO1 && BO1->getOpcode() == Instruction::Sub) {
3420 C = BO1->getOperand(0);
3421 D = BO1->getOperand(1);
3422 }
3423
3424 // icmp (X-Y), X -> icmp 0, Y for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3425 if (A == Op1 && NoOp0WrapProblem)
3426 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Constant::getNullValue(Op1->getType()), B);
3427 // icmp X, (X-Y) -> icmp Y, 0 for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3428 if (C == Op0 && NoOp1WrapProblem)
3429 return new ICmpInst(Pred, D, Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType()));
3430
3431 // (A - B) >u A --> A <u B
3432 if (A == Op1 && Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
3433 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, A, B);
3434 // C <u (C - D) --> C <u D
3435 if (C == Op0 && Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
3436 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, C, D);
3437
3438 // icmp (Y-X), (Z-X) -> icmp Y, Z for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3439 if (B && D && B == D && NoOp0WrapProblem && NoOp1WrapProblem &&
3440 // Try not to increase register pressure.
3441 BO0->hasOneUse() && BO1->hasOneUse())
3442 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, C);
3443 // icmp (X-Y), (X-Z) -> icmp Z, Y for equalities or if there is no overflow.
3444 if (A && C && A == C && NoOp0WrapProblem && NoOp1WrapProblem &&
3445 // Try not to increase register pressure.
3446 BO0->hasOneUse() && BO1->hasOneUse())
3447 return new ICmpInst(Pred, D, B);
3448
3449 // icmp (0-X) < cst --> x > -cst
3450 if (NoOp0WrapProblem && ICmpInst::isSigned(Pred)) {
3451 Value *X;
3452 if (match(BO0, m_Neg(m_Value(X))))
3453 if (Constant *RHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op1))
3454 if (RHSC->isNotMinSignedValue())
3455 return new ICmpInst(I.getSwappedPredicate(), X,
3456 ConstantExpr::getNeg(RHSC));
3457 }
3458
3459 BinaryOperator *SRem = nullptr;
3460 // icmp (srem X, Y), Y
3461 if (BO0 && BO0->getOpcode() == Instruction::SRem && Op1 == BO0->getOperand(1))
3462 SRem = BO0;
3463 // icmp Y, (srem X, Y)
3464 else if (BO1 && BO1->getOpcode() == Instruction::SRem &&
3465 Op0 == BO1->getOperand(1))
3466 SRem = BO1;
3467 if (SRem) {
3468 // We don't check hasOneUse to avoid increasing register pressure because
3469 // the value we use is the same value this instruction was already using.
3470 switch (SRem == BO0 ? ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred) : Pred) {
3471 default:
3472 break;
3473 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
3474 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
3475 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
3476 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
3477 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
3478 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
3479 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, SRem->getOperand(1),
3480 Constant::getAllOnesValue(SRem->getType()));
3481 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
3482 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
3483 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, SRem->getOperand(1),
3484 Constant::getNullValue(SRem->getType()));
3485 }
3486 }
3487
3488 if (BO0 && BO1 && BO0->getOpcode() == BO1->getOpcode() && BO0->hasOneUse() &&
3489 BO1->hasOneUse() && BO0->getOperand(1) == BO1->getOperand(1)) {
3490 switch (BO0->getOpcode()) {
3491 default:
3492 break;
3493 case Instruction::Add:
3494 case Instruction::Sub:
3495 case Instruction::Xor: {
3496 if (I.isEquality()) // a+x icmp eq/ne b+x --> a icmp b
3497 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3498
3499 const APInt *C;
3500 if (match(BO0->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
3501 // icmp u/s (a ^ signmask), (b ^ signmask) --> icmp s/u a, b
3502 if (C->isSignMask()) {
3503 ICmpInst::Predicate NewPred =
3504 I.isSigned() ? I.getUnsignedPredicate() : I.getSignedPredicate();
3505 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3506 }
3507
3508 // icmp u/s (a ^ maxsignval), (b ^ maxsignval) --> icmp s/u' a, b
3509 if (BO0->getOpcode() == Instruction::Xor && C->isMaxSignedValue()) {
3510 ICmpInst::Predicate NewPred =
3511 I.isSigned() ? I.getUnsignedPredicate() : I.getSignedPredicate();
3512 NewPred = I.getSwappedPredicate(NewPred);
3513 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3514 }
3515 }
3516 break;
3517 }
3518 case Instruction::Mul: {
3519 if (!I.isEquality())
3520 break;
3521
3522 const APInt *C;
3523 if (match(BO0->getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isNullValue() &&
3524 !C->isOneValue()) {
3525 // icmp eq/ne (X * C), (Y * C) --> icmp (X & Mask), (Y & Mask)
3526 // Mask = -1 >> count-trailing-zeros(C).
3527 if (unsigned TZs = C->countTrailingZeros()) {
3528 Constant *Mask = ConstantInt::get(
3529 BO0->getType(),
3530 APInt::getLowBitsSet(C->getBitWidth(), C->getBitWidth() - TZs));
3531 Value *And1 = Builder.CreateAnd(BO0->getOperand(0), Mask);
3532 Value *And2 = Builder.CreateAnd(BO1->getOperand(0), Mask);
3533 return new ICmpInst(Pred, And1, And2);
3534 }
3535 // If there are no trailing zeros in the multiplier, just eliminate
3536 // the multiplies (no masking is needed):
3537 // icmp eq/ne (X * C), (Y * C) --> icmp eq/ne X, Y
3538 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3539 }
3540 break;
3541 }
3542 case Instruction::UDiv:
3543 case Instruction::LShr:
3544 if (I.isSigned() || !BO0->isExact() || !BO1->isExact())
3545 break;
3546 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3547
3548 case Instruction::SDiv:
3549 if (!I.isEquality() || !BO0->isExact() || !BO1->isExact())
3550 break;
3551 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3552
3553 case Instruction::AShr:
3554 if (!BO0->isExact() || !BO1->isExact())
3555 break;
3556 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3557
3558 case Instruction::Shl: {
3559 bool NUW = BO0->hasNoUnsignedWrap() && BO1->hasNoUnsignedWrap();
3560 bool NSW = BO0->hasNoSignedWrap() && BO1->hasNoSignedWrap();
3561 if (!NUW && !NSW)
3562 break;
3563 if (!NSW && I.isSigned())
3564 break;
3565 return new ICmpInst(Pred, BO0->getOperand(0), BO1->getOperand(0));
3566 }
3567 }
3568 }
3569
3570 if (BO0) {
3571 // Transform A & (L - 1) `ult` L --> L != 0
3572 auto LSubOne = m_Add(m_Specific(Op1), m_AllOnes());
3573 auto BitwiseAnd = m_c_And(m_Value(), LSubOne);
3574
3575 if (match(BO0, BitwiseAnd) && Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT) {
3576 auto *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(BO0->getType());
3577 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op1, Zero);
3578 }
3579 }
3580
3581 if (Value *V = foldICmpWithLowBitMaskedVal(I, Builder))
3582 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, V);
3583
3584 if (Value *V = foldICmpWithTruncSignExtendedVal(I, Builder))
3585 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, V);
3586
3587 return nullptr;
3588}
