3590/// Fold icmp Pred min|max(X, Y), X.
3591static Instruction *foldICmpWithMinMax(ICmpInst &Cmp) {
3592 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = Cmp.getPredicate();
3593 Value *Op0 = Cmp.getOperand(0);
3594 Value *X = Cmp.getOperand(1);
3595
3596 // Canonicalize minimum or maximum operand to LHS of the icmp.
3597 if (match(X, m_c_SMin(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value())) ||
3598 match(X, m_c_SMax(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value())) ||
3599 match(X, m_c_UMin(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value())) ||
3600 match(X, m_c_UMax(m_Specific(Op0), m_Value()))) {
3601 std::swap(Op0, X);
3602 Pred = Cmp.getSwappedPredicate();
3603 }
3604
3605 Value *Y;
3606 if (match(Op0, m_c_SMin(m_Specific(X), m_Value(Y)))) {
3607 // smin(X, Y) == X --> X s<= Y
3608 // smin(X, Y) s>= X --> X s<= Y
3609 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
3610 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE, X, Y);
3611
3612 // smin(X, Y) != X --> X s> Y
3613 // smin(X, Y) s< X --> X s> Y
3614 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
3615 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, X, Y);
3616
3617 // These cases should be handled in InstSimplify:
3618 // smin(X, Y) s<= X --> true
3619 // smin(X, Y) s> X --> false
3620 return nullptr;
3621 }
3622
3623 if (match(Op0, m_c_SMax(m_Specific(X), m_Value(Y)))) {
3624 // smax(X, Y) == X --> X s>= Y
3625 // smax(X, Y) s<= X --> X s>= Y
3626 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
3627 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE, X, Y);
3628
3629 // smax(X, Y) != X --> X s< Y
3630 // smax(X, Y) s> X --> X s< Y
3631 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
3632 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, X, Y);
3633
3634 // These cases should be handled in InstSimplify:
3635 // smax(X, Y) s>= X --> true
3636 // smax(X, Y) s< X --> false
3637 return nullptr;
3638 }
3639
3640 if (match(Op0, m_c_UMin(m_Specific(X), m_Value(Y)))) {
3641 // umin(X, Y) == X --> X u<= Y
3642 // umin(X, Y) u>= X --> X u<= Y
3643 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
3644 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE, X, Y);
3645
3646 // umin(X, Y) != X --> X u> Y
3647 // umin(X, Y) u< X --> X u> Y
3648 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
3649 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT, X, Y);
3650
3651 // These cases should be handled in InstSimplify:
3652 // umin(X, Y) u<= X --> true
3653 // umin(X, Y) u> X --> false
3654 return nullptr;
3655 }
3656
3657 if (match(Op0, m_c_UMax(m_Specific(X), m_Value(Y)))) {
3658 // umax(X, Y) == X --> X u>= Y
3659 // umax(X, Y) u<= X --> X u>= Y
3660 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
3661 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE, X, Y);
3662
3663 // umax(X, Y) != X --> X u< Y
3664 // umax(X, Y) u> X --> X u< Y
3665 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
3666 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT, X, Y);
3667
3668 // These cases should be handled in InstSimplify:
3669 // umax(X, Y) u>= X --> true
3670 // umax(X, Y) u< X --> false
3671 return nullptr;
3672 }
3673
3674 return nullptr;
3675}
3676
3677Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpEquality(ICmpInst &I) {
3678 if (!I.isEquality())
3679 return nullptr;
3680
3681 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
3682 const CmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
3683 Value *A, *B, *C, *D;
3684 if (match(Op0, m_Xor(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) {
3685 if (A == Op1 || B == Op1) { // (A^B) == A -> B == 0
3686 Value *OtherVal = A == Op1 ? B : A;
3687 return new ICmpInst(Pred, OtherVal, Constant::getNullValue(A->getType()));
3688 }
3689
3690 if (match(Op1, m_Xor(m_Value(C), m_Value(D)))) {
3691 // A^c1 == C^c2 --> A == C^(c1^c2)
3692 ConstantInt *C1, *C2;
3693 if (match(B, m_ConstantInt(C1)) && match(D, m_ConstantInt(C2)) &&
3694 Op1->hasOneUse()) {
3695 Constant *NC = Builder.getInt(C1->getValue() ^ C2->getValue());
3696 Value *Xor = Builder.CreateXor(C, NC);
3697 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, Xor);
3698 }
3699
3700 // A^B == A^D -> B == D
3701 if (A == C)
3702 return new ICmpInst(Pred, B, D);
3703 if (A == D)
3704 return new ICmpInst(Pred, B, C);
3705 if (B == C)
3706 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, D);
3707 if (B == D)
3708 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, C);
3709 }
3710 }
3711
3712 if (match(Op1, m_Xor(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) && (A == Op0 || B == Op0)) {
3713 // A == (A^B) -> B == 0
3714 Value *OtherVal = A == Op0 ? B : A;
3715 return new ICmpInst(Pred, OtherVal, Constant::getNullValue(A->getType()));
3716 }
3717
3718 // (X&Z) == (Y&Z) -> (X^Y) & Z == 0
3719 if (match(Op0, m_OneUse(m_And(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) &&
3720 match(Op1, m_OneUse(m_And(m_Value(C), m_Value(D))))) {
3721 Value *X = nullptr, *Y = nullptr, *Z = nullptr;
3722
3723 if (A == C) {
3724 X = B;
3725 Y = D;
3726 Z = A;
3727 } else if (A == D) {
3728 X = B;
3729 Y = C;
3730 Z = A;
3731 } else if (B == C) {
3732 X = A;
3733 Y = D;
3734 Z = B;
3735 } else if (B == D) {
3736 X = A;
3737 Y = C;
3738 Z = B;
3739 }
3740
3741 if (X) { // Build (X^Y) & Z
3742 Op1 = Builder.CreateXor(X, Y);
3743 Op1 = Builder.CreateAnd(Op1, Z);
3744 I.setOperand(0, Op1);
3745 I.setOperand(1, Constant::getNullValue(Op1->getType()));
3746 return &I;
3747 }
3748 }
3749
3750 // Transform (zext A) == (B & (1<<X)-1) --> A == (trunc B)
3751 // and (B & (1<<X)-1) == (zext A) --> A == (trunc B)
3752 ConstantInt *Cst1;
3753 if ((Op0->hasOneUse() && match(Op0, m_ZExt(m_Value(A))) &&
3754 match(Op1, m_And(m_Value(B), m_ConstantInt(Cst1)))) ||
3755 (Op1->hasOneUse() && match(Op0, m_And(m_Value(B), m_ConstantInt(Cst1))) &&
3756 match(Op1, m_ZExt(m_Value(A))))) {
3757 APInt Pow2 = Cst1->getValue() + 1;
3758 if (Pow2.isPowerOf2() && isa<IntegerType>(A->getType()) &&
3759 Pow2.logBase2() == cast<IntegerType>(A->getType())->getBitWidth())
3760 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, Builder.CreateTrunc(B, A->getType()));
3761 }
3762
3763 // (A >> C) == (B >> C) --> (A^B) u< (1 << C)
3764 // For lshr and ashr pairs.
3765 if ((match(Op0, m_OneUse(m_LShr(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(Cst1)))) &&
3766 match(Op1, m_OneUse(m_LShr(m_Value(B), m_Specific(Cst1))))) ||
3767 (match(Op0, m_OneUse(m_AShr(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(Cst1)))) &&
3768 match(Op1, m_OneUse(m_AShr(m_Value(B), m_Specific(Cst1)))))) {
3769 unsigned TypeBits = Cst1->getBitWidth();
3770 unsigned ShAmt = (unsigned)Cst1->getLimitedValue(TypeBits);
3771 if (ShAmt < TypeBits && ShAmt != 0) {
3772 ICmpInst::Predicate NewPred =
3773 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
3774 Value *Xor = Builder.CreateXor(A, B, I.getName() + ".unshifted");
3775 APInt CmpVal = APInt::getOneBitSet(TypeBits, ShAmt);
3776 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, Xor, Builder.getInt(CmpVal));
3777 }
3778 }
3779
3780 // (A << C) == (B << C) --> ((A^B) & (~0U >> C)) == 0
3781 if (match(Op0, m_OneUse(m_Shl(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(Cst1)))) &&
3782 match(Op1, m_OneUse(m_Shl(m_Value(B), m_Specific(Cst1))))) {
3783 unsigned TypeBits = Cst1->getBitWidth();
3784 unsigned ShAmt = (unsigned)Cst1->getLimitedValue(TypeBits);
3785 if (ShAmt < TypeBits && ShAmt != 0) {
3786 Value *Xor = Builder.CreateXor(A, B, I.getName() + ".unshifted");
3787 APInt AndVal = APInt::getLowBitsSet(TypeBits, TypeBits - ShAmt);
3788 Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(Xor, Builder.getInt(AndVal),
3789 I.getName() + ".mask");
3790 return new ICmpInst(Pred, And, Constant::getNullValue(Cst1->getType()));
3791 }
3792 }
3793
3794 // Transform "icmp eq (trunc (lshr(X, cst1)), cst" to
3795 // "icmp (and X, mask), cst"
3796 uint64_t ShAmt = 0;
3797 if (Op0->hasOneUse() &&
3798 match(Op0, m_Trunc(m_OneUse(m_LShr(m_Value(A), m_ConstantInt(ShAmt))))) &&
3799 match(Op1, m_ConstantInt(Cst1)) &&
3800 // Only do this when A has multiple uses. This is most important to do
3801 // when it exposes other optimizations.
3802 !A->hasOneUse()) {
3803 unsigned ASize = cast<IntegerType>(A->getType())->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
3804
3805 if (ShAmt < ASize) {
3806 APInt MaskV =
3807 APInt::getLowBitsSet(ASize, Op0->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
3808 MaskV <<= ShAmt;
3809
3810 APInt CmpV = Cst1->getValue().zext(ASize);
3811 CmpV <<= ShAmt;
3812
3813 Value *Mask = Builder.CreateAnd(A, Builder.getInt(MaskV));
3814 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Mask, Builder.getInt(CmpV));
3815 }
3816 }
3817
3818 // If both operands are byte-swapped or bit-reversed, just compare the
3819 // original values.
3820 // TODO: Move this to a function similar to foldICmpIntrinsicWithConstant()
3821 // and handle more intrinsics.
3822 if ((match(Op0, m_BSwap(m_Value(A))) && match(Op1, m_BSwap(m_Value(B)))) ||
3823 (match(Op0, m_BitReverse(m_Value(A))) &&
3824 match(Op1, m_BitReverse(m_Value(B)))))
3825 return new ICmpInst(Pred, A, B);
3826
3827 return nullptr;
3828}
3829
3830/// Handle icmp (cast x to y), (cast/cst). We only handle extending casts so
3831/// far.
3832Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpWithCastAndCast(ICmpInst &ICmp) {
3833 const CastInst *LHSCI = cast<CastInst>(ICmp.getOperand(0));
3834 Value *LHSCIOp = LHSCI->getOperand(0);
3835 Type *SrcTy = LHSCIOp->getType();
3836 Type *DestTy = LHSCI->getType();
3837
3838 // Turn icmp (ptrtoint x), (ptrtoint/c) into a compare of the input if the
3839 // integer type is the same size as the pointer type.
3840 const auto& CompatibleSizes = [&](Type* SrcTy, Type* DestTy) -> bool {
3841 if (isa<VectorType>(SrcTy)) {
3842 SrcTy = cast<VectorType>(SrcTy)->getElementType();
3843 DestTy = cast<VectorType>(DestTy)->getElementType();
3844 }
3845 return DL.getPointerTypeSizeInBits(SrcTy) == DestTy->getIntegerBitWidth();
3846 };
3847 if (LHSCI->getOpcode() == Instruction::PtrToInt &&
3848 CompatibleSizes(SrcTy, DestTy)) {
3849 Value *RHSOp = nullptr;
3850 if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<PtrToIntOperator>(ICmp.getOperand(1))) {
3851 Value *RHSCIOp = RHSC->getOperand(0);
3852 if (RHSCIOp->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
3853 LHSCIOp->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) {
3854 RHSOp = RHSC->getOperand(0);
3855 // If the pointer types don't match, insert a bitcast.
3856 if (LHSCIOp->getType() != RHSOp->getType())
3857 RHSOp = Builder.CreateBitCast(RHSOp, LHSCIOp->getType());
3858 }
3859 } else if (auto *RHSC = dyn_cast<Constant>(ICmp.getOperand(1))) {
3860 RHSOp = ConstantExpr::getIntToPtr(RHSC, SrcTy);
3861 }
3862
3863 if (RHSOp)
3864 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getPredicate(), LHSCIOp, RHSOp);
3865 }
3866
3867 // The code below only handles extension cast instructions, so far.
3868 // Enforce this.
3869 if (LHSCI->getOpcode() != Instruction::ZExt &&
3870 LHSCI->getOpcode() != Instruction::SExt)
3871 return nullptr;
3872
3873 bool isSignedExt = LHSCI->getOpcode() == Instruction::SExt;
3874 bool isSignedCmp = ICmp.isSigned();
3875
3876 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(ICmp.getOperand(1))) {
3877 // Not an extension from the same type?
3878 Value *RHSCIOp = CI->getOperand(0);
3879 if (RHSCIOp->getType() != LHSCIOp->getType())
3880 return nullptr;
3881
3882 // If the signedness of the two casts doesn't agree (i.e. one is a sext
3883 // and the other is a zext), then we can't handle this.
3884 if (CI->getOpcode() != LHSCI->getOpcode())
3885 return nullptr;
3886
3887 // Deal with equality cases early.
3888 if (ICmp.isEquality())
3889 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getPredicate(), LHSCIOp, RHSCIOp);
3890
3891 // A signed comparison of sign extended values simplifies into a
3892 // signed comparison.
3893 if (isSignedCmp && isSignedExt)
3894 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getPredicate(), LHSCIOp, RHSCIOp);
3895
3896 // The other three cases all fold into an unsigned comparison.
3897 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getUnsignedPredicate(), LHSCIOp, RHSCIOp);
3898 }
3899
3900 // If we aren't dealing with a constant on the RHS, exit early.
3901 auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(ICmp.getOperand(1));
3902 if (!C)
3903 return nullptr;
3904
3905 // Compute the constant that would happen if we truncated to SrcTy then
3906 // re-extended to DestTy.
3907 Constant *Res1 = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy);
3908 Constant *Res2 = ConstantExpr::getCast(LHSCI->getOpcode(), Res1, DestTy);
3909
3910 // If the re-extended constant didn't change...
3911 if (Res2 == C) {
3912 // Deal with equality cases early.
3913 if (ICmp.isEquality())
3914 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getPredicate(), LHSCIOp, Res1);
3915
3916 // A signed comparison of sign extended values simplifies into a
3917 // signed comparison.
3918 if (isSignedExt && isSignedCmp)
3919 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getPredicate(), LHSCIOp, Res1);
3920
3921 // The other three cases all fold into an unsigned comparison.
3922 return new ICmpInst(ICmp.getUnsignedPredicate(), LHSCIOp, Res1);
3923 }
3924
3925 // The re-extended constant changed, partly changed (in the case of a vector),
3926 // or could not be determined to be equal (in the case of a constant
3927 // expression), so the constant cannot be represented in the shorter type.
3928 // Consequently, we cannot emit a simple comparison.
3929 // All the cases that fold to true or false will have already been handled
3930 // by SimplifyICmpInst, so only deal with the tricky case.
3931
3932 if (isSignedCmp || !isSignedExt || !isa<ConstantInt>(C))
3933 return nullptr;
3934
3935 // Evaluate the comparison for LT (we invert for GT below). LE and GE cases
3936 // should have been folded away previously and not enter in here.
3937
3938 // We're performing an unsigned comp with a sign extended value.
3939 // This is true if the input is >= 0. [aka >s -1]
3940 Constant *NegOne = Constant::getAllOnesValue(SrcTy);
3941 Value *Result = Builder.CreateICmpSGT(LHSCIOp, NegOne, ICmp.getName());
3942
3943 // Finally, return the value computed.
3944 if (ICmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
3945 return replaceInstUsesWith(ICmp, Result);
3946
3947 assert(ICmp.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && "ICmp should be folded!");
3948 return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(Result);
3949}
3950
3951static bool isNeutralValue(Instruction::BinaryOps BinaryOp, Value *RHS) {
3952 switch (BinaryOp) {
3953 default:
3954 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported binary op");
3955 case Instruction::Add:
3956 case Instruction::Sub:
3957 return match(RHS, m_Zero());
3958 case Instruction::Mul:
3959 return match(RHS, m_One());
3960 }
3961}
3962
3963OverflowResult InstCombiner::computeOverflow(
3964 Instruction::BinaryOps BinaryOp, bool IsSigned,
3965 Value *LHS, Value *RHS, Instruction *CxtI) const {
3966 switch (BinaryOp) {
3967 default:
3968 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported binary op");
3969 case Instruction::Add:
3970 if (IsSigned)
3971 return computeOverflowForSignedAdd(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3972 else
3973 return computeOverflowForUnsignedAdd(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3974 case Instruction::Sub:
3975 if (IsSigned)
3976 return computeOverflowForSignedSub(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3977 else
3978 return computeOverflowForUnsignedSub(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3979 case Instruction::Mul:
3980 if (IsSigned)
3981 return computeOverflowForSignedMul(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3982 else
3983 return computeOverflowForUnsignedMul(LHS, RHS, CxtI);
3984 }
3985}
3986
3987bool InstCombiner::OptimizeOverflowCheck(
3988 Instruction::BinaryOps BinaryOp, bool IsSigned, Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
3989 Instruction &OrigI, Value *&Result, Constant *&Overflow) {
3990 if (OrigI.isCommutative() && isa<Constant>(LHS) && !isa<Constant>(RHS))
3991 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
3992
3993 // If the overflow check was an add followed by a compare, the insertion point
3994 // may be pointing to the compare. We want to insert the new instructions
3995 // before the add in case there are uses of the add between the add and the
3996 // compare.
3997 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&OrigI);
3998
3999 if (isNeutralValue(BinaryOp, RHS)) {
4000 Result = LHS;
4001 Overflow = Builder.getFalse();
4002 return true;
4003 }
4004
4005 switch (computeOverflow(BinaryOp, IsSigned, LHS, RHS, &OrigI)) {
4006 case OverflowResult::MayOverflow:
4007 return false;
4008 case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsLow:
4009 case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsHigh:
4010 Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(BinaryOp, LHS, RHS);
4011 Result->takeName(&OrigI);
4012 Overflow = Builder.getTrue();
4013 return true;
4014 case OverflowResult::NeverOverflows:
4015 Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(BinaryOp, LHS, RHS);
4016 Result->takeName(&OrigI);
4017 Overflow = Builder.getFalse();
4018 if (auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Result)) {
4019 if (IsSigned)
4020 Inst->setHasNoSignedWrap();
4021 else
4022 Inst->setHasNoUnsignedWrap();
4023 }
4024 return true;
4025 }
4026
4027 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected overflow result");
4028}
4029
4030/// Recognize and process idiom involving test for multiplication
4031/// overflow.
4032///
4033/// The caller has matched a pattern of the form:
4034/// I = cmp u (mul(zext A, zext B), V
4035/// The function checks if this is a test for overflow and if so replaces
4036/// multiplication with call to 'mul.with.overflow' intrinsic.
4037///
4038/// \param I Compare instruction.
4039/// \param MulVal Result of 'mult' instruction. It is one of the arguments of
4040/// the compare instruction. Must be of integer type.
4041/// \param OtherVal The other argument of compare instruction.
4042/// \returns Instruction which must replace the compare instruction, NULL if no
4043/// replacement required.
4044static Instruction *processUMulZExtIdiom(ICmpInst &I, Value *MulVal,
4045 Value *OtherVal, InstCombiner &IC) {
4046 // Don't bother doing this transformation for pointers, don't do it for
4047 // vectors.
4048 if (!isa<IntegerType>(MulVal->getType()))
4049 return nullptr;
4050
4051 assert(I.getOperand(0) == MulVal || I.getOperand(1) == MulVal);
4052 assert(I.getOperand(0) == OtherVal || I.getOperand(1) == OtherVal);
4053 auto *MulInstr = dyn_cast<Instruction>(MulVal);
4054 if (!MulInstr)
4055 return nullptr;
4056 assert(MulInstr->getOpcode() == Instruction::Mul);
4057
4058 auto *LHS = cast<ZExtOperator>(MulInstr->getOperand(0)),
4059 *RHS = cast<ZExtOperator>(MulInstr->getOperand(1));
4060 assert(LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::ZExt);
4061 assert(RHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::ZExt);
4062 Value *A = LHS->getOperand(0), *B = RHS->getOperand(0);
4063
4064 // Calculate type and width of the result produced by mul.with.overflow.
4065 Type *TyA = A->getType(), *TyB = B->getType();
4066 unsigned WidthA = TyA->getPrimitiveSizeInBits(),
4067 WidthB = TyB->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
4068 unsigned MulWidth;
4069 Type *MulType;
4070 if (WidthB > WidthA) {
4071 MulWidth = WidthB;
4072 MulType = TyB;
4073 } else {
4074 MulWidth = WidthA;
4075 MulType = TyA;
4076 }
4077
4078 // In order to replace the original mul with a narrower mul.with.overflow,
4079 // all uses must ignore upper bits of the product. The number of used low
4080 // bits must be not greater than the width of mul.with.overflow.
4081 if (MulVal->hasNUsesOrMore(2))
4082 for (User *U : MulVal->users()) {
4083 if (U == &I)
4084 continue;
4085 if (TruncInst *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(U)) {
4086 // Check if truncation ignores bits above MulWidth.
4087 unsigned TruncWidth = TI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
4088 if (TruncWidth > MulWidth)
4089 return nullptr;
4090 } else if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(U)) {
4091 // Check if AND ignores bits above MulWidth.
4092 if (BO->getOpcode() != Instruction::And)
4093 return nullptr;
4094 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(BO->getOperand(1))) {
4095 const APInt &CVal = CI->getValue();
4096 if (CVal.getBitWidth() - CVal.countLeadingZeros() > MulWidth)
4097 return nullptr;
4098 } else {
4099 // In this case we could have the operand of the binary operation
4100 // being defined in another block, and performing the replacement
4101 // could break the dominance relation.
4102 return nullptr;
4103 }
4104 } else {
4105 // Other uses prohibit this transformation.
4106 return nullptr;
4107 }
4108 }
4109
4110 // Recognize patterns
4111 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4112 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
4113 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
4114 // Recognize pattern:
4115 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4116 // cmp eq/neq mulval, zext trunc mulval
4117 if (ZExtInst *Zext = dyn_cast<ZExtInst>(OtherVal))
4118 if (Zext->hasOneUse()) {
4119 Value *ZextArg = Zext->getOperand(0);
4120 if (TruncInst *Trunc = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(ZextArg))
4121 if (Trunc->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == MulWidth)
4122 break; //Recognized
4123 }
4124
4125 // Recognize pattern:
4126 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4127 // cmp eq/neq mulval, and(mulval, mask), mask selects low MulWidth bits.
4128 ConstantInt *CI;
4129 Value *ValToMask;
4130 if (match(OtherVal, m_And(m_Value(ValToMask), m_ConstantInt(CI)))) {
4131 if (ValToMask != MulVal)
4132 return nullptr;
4133 const APInt &CVal = CI->getValue() + 1;
4134 if (CVal.isPowerOf2()) {
4135 unsigned MaskWidth = CVal.logBase2();
4136 if (MaskWidth == MulWidth)
4137 break; // Recognized
4138 }
4139 }
4140 return nullptr;
4141
4142 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4143 // Recognize pattern:
4144 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4145 // cmp ugt mulval, max
4146 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(OtherVal)) {
4147 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getMaxValue(MulWidth);
4148 MaxVal = MaxVal.zext(CI->getBitWidth());
4149 if (MaxVal.eq(CI->getValue()))
4150 break; // Recognized
4151 }
4152 return nullptr;
4153
4154 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4155 // Recognize pattern:
4156 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4157 // cmp uge mulval, max+1
4158 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(OtherVal)) {
4159 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getOneBitSet(CI->getBitWidth(), MulWidth);
4160 if (MaxVal.eq(CI->getValue()))
4161 break; // Recognized
4162 }
4163 return nullptr;
4164
4165 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4166 // Recognize pattern:
4167 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4168 // cmp ule mulval, max
4169 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(OtherVal)) {
4170 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getMaxValue(MulWidth);
4171 MaxVal = MaxVal.zext(CI->getBitWidth());
4172 if (MaxVal.eq(CI->getValue()))
4173 break; // Recognized
4174 }
4175 return nullptr;
4176
4177 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4178 // Recognize pattern:
4179 // mulval = mul(zext A, zext B)
4180 // cmp ule mulval, max + 1
4181 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(OtherVal)) {
4182 APInt MaxVal = APInt::getOneBitSet(CI->getBitWidth(), MulWidth);
4183 if (MaxVal.eq(CI->getValue()))
4184 break; // Recognized
4185 }
4186 return nullptr;
4187
4188 default:
4189 return nullptr;
4190 }
4191
4192 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder = IC.Builder;
4193 Builder.SetInsertPoint(MulInstr);
4194
4195 // Replace: mul(zext A, zext B) --> mul.with.overflow(A, B)
4196 Value *MulA = A, *MulB = B;
4197 if (WidthA < MulWidth)
4198 MulA = Builder.CreateZExt(A, MulType);
4199 if (WidthB < MulWidth)
4200 MulB = Builder.CreateZExt(B, MulType);
4201 Function *F = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
4202 I.getModule(), Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow, MulType);
4203 CallInst *Call = Builder.CreateCall(F, {MulA, MulB}, "umul");
4204 IC.Worklist.Add(MulInstr);
4205
4206 // If there are uses of mul result other than the comparison, we know that
4207 // they are truncation or binary AND. Change them to use result of
4208 // mul.with.overflow and adjust properly mask/size.
4209 if (MulVal->hasNUsesOrMore(2)) {
4210 Value *Mul = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 0, "umul.value");
4211 for (auto UI = MulVal->user_begin(), UE = MulVal->user_end(); UI != UE;) {
4212 User *U = *UI++;
4213 if (U == &I || U == OtherVal)
4214 continue;
4215 if (TruncInst *TI = dyn_cast<TruncInst>(U)) {
4216 if (TI->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == MulWidth)
4217 IC.replaceInstUsesWith(*TI, Mul);
4218 else
4219 TI->setOperand(0, Mul);
4220 } else if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(U)) {
4221 assert(BO->getOpcode() == Instruction::And);
4222 // Replace (mul & mask) --> zext (mul.with.overflow & short_mask)
4223 ConstantInt *CI = cast<ConstantInt>(BO->getOperand(1));
4224 APInt ShortMask = CI->getValue().trunc(MulWidth);
4225 Value *ShortAnd = Builder.CreateAnd(Mul, ShortMask);
4226 Instruction *Zext =
4227 cast<Instruction>(Builder.CreateZExt(ShortAnd, BO->getType()));
4228 IC.Worklist.Add(Zext);
4229 IC.replaceInstUsesWith(*BO, Zext);
4230 } else {
4231 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected Binary operation");
4232 }
4233 IC.Worklist.Add(cast<Instruction>(U));
4234 }
4235 }
4236 if (isa<Instruction>(OtherVal))
4237 IC.Worklist.Add(cast<Instruction>(OtherVal));
4238
4239 // The original icmp gets replaced with the overflow value, maybe inverted
4240 // depending on predicate.
4241 bool Inverse = false;
4242 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4243 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
4244 break;
4245 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
4246 Inverse = true;
4247 break;
4248 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4249 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4250 if (I.getOperand(0) == MulVal)
4251 break;
4252 Inverse = true;
4253 break;
4254 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4255 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4256 if (I.getOperand(1) == MulVal)
4257 break;
4258 Inverse = true;
4259 break;
4260 default:
4261 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected predicate");
4262 }
4263 if (Inverse) {
4264 Value *Res = Builder.CreateExtractValue(Call, 1);
4265 return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(Res);
4266 }
4267
4268 return ExtractValueInst::Create(Call, 1);
4269}
4270
4271/// When performing a comparison against a constant, it is possible that not all
4272/// the bits in the LHS are demanded. This helper method computes the mask that
4273/// IS demanded.
4274static APInt getDemandedBitsLHSMask(ICmpInst &I, unsigned BitWidth) {
4275 const APInt *RHS;
4276 if (!match(I.getOperand(1), m_APInt(RHS)))
4277 return APInt::getAllOnesValue(BitWidth);
4278
4279 // If this is a normal comparison, it demands all bits. If it is a sign bit
4280 // comparison, it only demands the sign bit.
4281 bool UnusedBit;
4282 if (isSignBitCheck(I.getPredicate(), *RHS, UnusedBit))
4283 return APInt::getSignMask(BitWidth);
4284
4285 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4286 // For a UGT comparison, we don't care about any bits that
4287 // correspond to the trailing ones of the comparand. The value of these
4288 // bits doesn't impact the outcome of the comparison, because any value
4289 // greater than the RHS must differ in a bit higher than these due to carry.
4290 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4291 return APInt::getBitsSetFrom(BitWidth, RHS->countTrailingOnes());
4292
4293 // Similarly, for a ULT comparison, we don't care about the trailing zeros.
4294 // Any value less than the RHS must differ in a higher bit because of carries.
4295 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4296 return APInt::getBitsSetFrom(BitWidth, RHS->countTrailingZeros());
4297
4298 default:
4299 return APInt::getAllOnesValue(BitWidth);
4300 }
4301}
4302
4303/// Check if the order of \p Op0 and \p Op1 as operands in an ICmpInst
4304/// should be swapped.
4305/// The decision is based on how many times these two operands are reused
4306/// as subtract operands and their positions in those instructions.
4307/// The rationale is that several architectures use the same instruction for
4308/// both subtract and cmp. Thus, it is better if the order of those operands
4309/// match.
4310/// \return true if Op0 and Op1 should be swapped.
4311static bool swapMayExposeCSEOpportunities(const Value *Op0, const Value *Op1) {
4312 // Filter out pointer values as those cannot appear directly in subtract.
4313 // FIXME: we may want to go through inttoptrs or bitcasts.
4314 if (Op0->getType()->isPointerTy())
4315 return false;
4316 // If a subtract already has the same operands as a compare, swapping would be
4317 // bad. If a subtract has the same operands as a compare but in reverse order,
4318 // then swapping is good.
4319 int GoodToSwap = 0;
4320 for (const User *U : Op0->users()) {
4321 if (match(U, m_Sub(m_Specific(Op1), m_Specific(Op0))))
4322 GoodToSwap++;
4323 else if (match(U, m_Sub(m_Specific(Op0), m_Specific(Op1))))
4324 GoodToSwap--;
4325 }
4326 return GoodToSwap > 0;
4327}
4328
4329/// Check that one use is in the same block as the definition and all
4330/// other uses are in blocks dominated by a given block.
4331///
4332/// \param DI Definition
4333/// \param UI Use
4334/// \param DB Block that must dominate all uses of \p DI outside
4335/// the parent block
4336/// \return true when \p UI is the only use of \p DI in the parent block
4337/// and all other uses of \p DI are in blocks dominated by \p DB.
4338///
4339bool InstCombiner::dominatesAllUses(const Instruction *DI,
4340 const Instruction *UI,
4341 const BasicBlock *DB) const {
4342 assert(DI && UI && "Instruction not defined\n");
4343 // Ignore incomplete definitions.
4344 if (!DI->getParent())
4345 return false;
4346 // DI and UI must be in the same block.
4347 if (DI->getParent() != UI->getParent())
4348 return false;
4349 // Protect from self-referencing blocks.
4350 if (DI->getParent() == DB)
4351 return false;
4352 for (const User *U : DI->users()) {
4353 auto *Usr = cast<Instruction>(U);
4354 if (Usr != UI && !DT.dominates(DB, Usr->getParent()))
4355 return false;
4356 }
4357 return true;
4358}
4359
4360/// Return true when the instruction sequence within a block is select-cmp-br.
4361static bool isChainSelectCmpBranch(const SelectInst *SI) {
4362 const BasicBlock *BB = SI->getParent();
4363 if (!BB)
4364 return false;
4365 auto *BI = dyn_cast_or_null<BranchInst>(BB->getTerminator());
4366 if (!BI || BI->getNumSuccessors() != 2)
4367 return false;
4368 auto *IC = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(BI->getCondition());
4369 if (!IC || (IC->getOperand(0) != SI && IC->getOperand(1) != SI))
4370 return false;
4371 return true;
4372}
4373
4374/// True when a select result is replaced by one of its operands
4375/// in select-icmp sequence. This will eventually result in the elimination
4376/// of the select.
4377///
4378/// \param SI Select instruction
4379/// \param Icmp Compare instruction
4380/// \param SIOpd Operand that replaces the select
4381///
4382/// Notes:
4383/// - The replacement is global and requires dominator information
4384/// - The caller is responsible for the actual replacement
4385///
4386/// Example:
4387///
4388/// entry:
4389/// %4 = select i1 %3, %C* %0, %C* null
4390/// %5 = icmp eq %C* %4, null
4391/// br i1 %5, label %9, label %7
4392/// ...
4393/// ; <label>:7 ; preds = %entry
4394/// %8 = getelementptr inbounds %C* %4, i64 0, i32 0
4395/// ...
4396///
4397/// can be transformed to
4398///
4399/// %5 = icmp eq %C* %0, null
4400/// %6 = select i1 %3, i1 %5, i1 true
4401/// br i1 %6, label %9, label %7
4402/// ...
4403/// ; <label>:7 ; preds = %entry
4404/// %8 = getelementptr inbounds %C* %0, i64 0, i32 0 // replace by %0!
4405///
4406/// Similar when the first operand of the select is a constant or/and
4407/// the compare is for not equal rather than equal.
4408///
4409/// NOTE: The function is only called when the select and compare constants
4410/// are equal, the optimization can work only for EQ predicates. This is not a
4411/// major restriction since a NE compare should be 'normalized' to an equal
4412/// compare, which usually happens in the combiner and test case
4413/// select-cmp-br.ll checks for it.
4414bool InstCombiner::replacedSelectWithOperand(SelectInst *SI,
4415 const ICmpInst *Icmp,
4416 const unsigned SIOpd) {
4417 assert((SIOpd == 1 || SIOpd == 2) && "Invalid select operand!");
4418 if (isChainSelectCmpBranch(SI) && Icmp->getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ) {
4419 BasicBlock *Succ = SI->getParent()->getTerminator()->getSuccessor(1);
4420 // The check for the single predecessor is not the best that can be
4421 // done. But it protects efficiently against cases like when SI's
4422 // home block has two successors, Succ and Succ1, and Succ1 predecessor
4423 // of Succ. Then SI can't be replaced by SIOpd because the use that gets
4424 // replaced can be reached on either path. So the uniqueness check
4425 // guarantees that the path all uses of SI (outside SI's parent) are on
4426 // is disjoint from all other paths out of SI. But that information
4427 // is more expensive to compute, and the trade-off here is in favor
4428 // of compile-time. It should also be noticed that we check for a single
4429 // predecessor and not only uniqueness. This to handle the situation when
4430 // Succ and Succ1 points to the same basic block.
4431 if (Succ->getSinglePredecessor() && dominatesAllUses(SI, Icmp, Succ)) {
4432 NumSel++;
4433 SI->replaceUsesOutsideBlock(SI->getOperand(SIOpd), SI->getParent());
4434 return true;
4435 }
4436 }
4437 return false;
4438}
4439
4440/// Try to fold the comparison based on range information we can get by checking
4441/// whether bits are known to be zero or one in the inputs.
4442Instruction *InstCombiner::foldICmpUsingKnownBits(ICmpInst &I) {
4443 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
4444 Type *Ty = Op0->getType();
4445 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
4446
4447 // Get scalar or pointer size.
4448 unsigned BitWidth = Ty->isIntOrIntVectorTy()
4449 ? Ty->getScalarSizeInBits()
4450 : DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(Ty->getScalarType());
4451
4452 if (!BitWidth)
4453 return nullptr;
4454
4455 KnownBits Op0Known(BitWidth);
4456 KnownBits Op1Known(BitWidth);
4457
4458 // Note: we can't do this for CHERI capabilities since the comparisons also
4459 // take the tag bit into account.
4460 //
4461 // For now just skip this optimization if one of the icmp operands is a CHERI
4462 // capability that might have the tag bit set.
4463 if (isCheriPointer(Ty, &DL)) {
4464 if (!(cheri::isKnownUntaggedCapability(I.getOperand(0), &DL) &&
4465 cheri::isKnownUntaggedCapability(I.getOperand(1), &DL))) {
4466 // At least one operand might be tagged -> we can't simplify this yet!
4467 return nullptr;
4468 } else {
4469 // convert the capability icmp to a vaddr icmp. The cheri_cap_address_get
4470 // Intrinsics will be removed if they refer to a constant value
4471 Builder.SetInsertPoint(&I);
4472 auto Addr1 = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get,
4473 DL.getIntPtrType(I.getOperand(0)->getType()), I.getOperand(0), nullptr, "op0_addr");
4474 auto Addr2 = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_address_get,
4475 DL.getIntPtrType(I.getOperand(0)->getType()), I.getOperand(1), nullptr, "op1_addr");
4476 I.setOperand(0, Addr1);
4477 I.setOperand(1, Addr2);
4478 }
4479 }
4480 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(&I, 0,
4481 getDemandedBitsLHSMask(I, BitWidth),
4482 Op0Known, 0))
4483 return &I;
4484
4485 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(&I, 1, APInt::getAllOnesValue(BitWidth),
4486 Op1Known, 0))
4487 return &I;
4488
4489 // Given the known and unknown bits, compute a range that the LHS could be
4490 // in. Compute the Min, Max and RHS values based on the known bits. For the
4491 // EQ and NE we use unsigned values.
4492 APInt Op0Min(BitWidth, 0), Op0Max(BitWidth, 0);
4493 APInt Op1Min(BitWidth, 0), Op1Max(BitWidth, 0);
4494 if (I.isSigned()) {
4495 computeSignedMinMaxValuesFromKnownBits(Op0Known, Op0Min, Op0Max);
4496 computeSignedMinMaxValuesFromKnownBits(Op1Known, Op1Min, Op1Max);
4497 } else {
4498 computeUnsignedMinMaxValuesFromKnownBits(Op0Known, Op0Min, Op0Max);
4499 computeUnsignedMinMaxValuesFromKnownBits(Op1Known, Op1Min, Op1Max);
4500 }
4501
4502 // If Min and Max are known to be the same, then SimplifyDemandedBits figured
4503 // out that the LHS or RHS is a constant. Constant fold this now, so that
4504 // code below can assume that Min != Max.
4505 if (!isa<Constant>(Op0) && Op0Min == Op0Max)
4506 return new ICmpInst(Pred, ConstantExpr::getIntegerValue(Ty, Op0Min), Op1);
4507 if (!isa<Constant>(Op1) && Op1Min == Op1Max)
4508 return new ICmpInst(Pred, Op0, ConstantExpr::getIntegerValue(Ty, Op1Min));
4509
4510 // Based on the range information we know about the LHS, see if we can
4511 // simplify this comparison. For example, (x&4) < 8 is always true.
4512 switch (Pred) {
4513 default:
4514 llvm_unreachable("Unknown icmp opcode!");
4515 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
4516 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE: {
4517 if (Op0Max.ult(Op1Min) || Op0Min.ugt(Op1Max)) {
4518 return Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ
4519 ? replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()))
4520 : replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4521 }
4522
4523 // If all bits are known zero except for one, then we know at most one bit
4524 // is set. If the comparison is against zero, then this is a check to see if
4525 // *that* bit is set.
4526 APInt Op0KnownZeroInverted = ~Op0Known.Zero;
4527 if (Op1Known.isZero()) {
4528 // If the LHS is an AND with the same constant, look through it.
4529 Value *LHS = nullptr;
4530 const APInt *LHSC;
4531 if (!match(Op0, m_And(m_Value(LHS), m_APInt(LHSC))) ||
4532 *LHSC != Op0KnownZeroInverted)
4533 LHS = Op0;
4534
4535 Value *X;
4536 if (match(LHS, m_Shl(m_One(), m_Value(X)))) {
4537 APInt ValToCheck = Op0KnownZeroInverted;
4538 Type *XTy = X->getType();
4539 if (ValToCheck.isPowerOf2()) {
4540 // ((1 << X) & 8) == 0 -> X != 3
4541 // ((1 << X) & 8) != 0 -> X == 3
4542 auto *CmpC = ConstantInt::get(XTy, ValToCheck.countTrailingZeros());
4543 auto NewPred = ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
4544 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, X, CmpC);
4545 } else if ((++ValToCheck).isPowerOf2()) {
4546 // ((1 << X) & 7) == 0 -> X >= 3
4547 // ((1 << X) & 7) != 0 -> X < 3
4548 auto *CmpC = ConstantInt::get(XTy, ValToCheck.countTrailingZeros());
4549 auto NewPred =
4550 Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ ? CmpInst::ICMP_UGE : CmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
4551 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, X, CmpC);
4552 }
4553 }
4554
4555 // Check if the LHS is 8 >>u x and the result is a power of 2 like 1.
4556 const APInt *CI;
4557 if (Op0KnownZeroInverted.isOneValue() &&
4558 match(LHS, m_LShr(m_Power2(CI), m_Value(X)))) {
4559 // ((8 >>u X) & 1) == 0 -> X != 3
4560 // ((8 >>u X) & 1) != 0 -> X == 3
4561 unsigned CmpVal = CI->countTrailingZeros();
4562 auto NewPred = ICmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
4563 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, X, ConstantInt::get(X->getType(), CmpVal));
4564 }
4565 }
4566 break;
4567 }
4568 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT: {
4569 if (Op0Max.ult(Op1Min)) // A <u B -> true if max(A) < min(B)
4570 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4571 if (Op0Min.uge(Op1Max)) // A <u B -> false if min(A) >= max(B)
4572 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4573 if (Op1Min == Op0Max) // A <u B -> A != B if max(A) == min(B)
4574 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op0, Op1);
4575
4576 const APInt *CmpC;
4577 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(CmpC))) {
4578 // A <u C -> A == C-1 if min(A)+1 == C
4579 if (*CmpC == Op0Min + 1)
4580 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0,
4581 ConstantInt::get(Op1->getType(), *CmpC - 1));
4582 // X <u C --> X == 0, if the number of zero bits in the bottom of X
4583 // exceeds the log2 of C.
4584 if (Op0Known.countMinTrailingZeros() >= CmpC->ceilLogBase2())
4585 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0,
4586 Constant::getNullValue(Op1->getType()));
4587 }
4588 break;
4589 }
4590 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT: {
4591 if (Op0Min.ugt(Op1Max)) // A >u B -> true if min(A) > max(B)
4592 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4593 if (Op0Max.ule(Op1Min)) // A >u B -> false if max(A) <= max(B)
4594 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4595 if (Op1Max == Op0Min) // A >u B -> A != B if min(A) == max(B)
4596 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op0, Op1);
4597
4598 const APInt *CmpC;
4599 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(CmpC))) {
4600 // A >u C -> A == C+1 if max(a)-1 == C
4601 if (*CmpC == Op0Max - 1)
4602 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0,
4603 ConstantInt::get(Op1->getType(), *CmpC + 1));
4604 // X >u C --> X != 0, if the number of zero bits in the bottom of X
4605 // exceeds the log2 of C.
4606 if (Op0Known.countMinTrailingZeros() >= CmpC->getActiveBits())
4607 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op0,
4608 Constant::getNullValue(Op1->getType()));
4609 }
4610 break;
4611 }
4612 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT: {
4613 if (Op0Max.slt(Op1Min)) // A <s B -> true if max(A) < min(C)
4614 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4615 if (Op0Min.sge(Op1Max)) // A <s B -> false if min(A) >= max(C)
4616 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4617 if (Op1Min == Op0Max) // A <s B -> A != B if max(A) == min(B)
4618 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op0, Op1);
4619 const APInt *CmpC;
4620 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(CmpC))) {
4621 if (*CmpC == Op0Min + 1) // A <s C -> A == C-1 if min(A)+1 == C
4622 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0,
4623 ConstantInt::get(Op1->getType(), *CmpC - 1));
4624 }
4625 break;
4626 }
4627 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT: {
4628 if (Op0Min.sgt(Op1Max)) // A >s B -> true if min(A) > max(B)
4629 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4630 if (Op0Max.sle(Op1Min)) // A >s B -> false if max(A) <= min(B)
4631 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4632 if (Op1Max == Op0Min) // A >s B -> A != B if min(A) == max(B)
4633 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, Op0, Op1);
4634 const APInt *CmpC;
4635 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(CmpC))) {
4636 if (*CmpC == Op0Max - 1) // A >s C -> A == C+1 if max(A)-1 == C
4637 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0,
4638 ConstantInt::get(Op1->getType(), *CmpC + 1));
4639 }
4640 break;
4641 }
4642 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
4643 assert(!isa<ConstantInt>(Op1) && "ICMP_SGE with ConstantInt not folded!");
4644 if (Op0Min.sge(Op1Max)) // A >=s B -> true if min(A) >= max(B)
4645 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4646 if (Op0Max.slt(Op1Min)) // A >=s B -> false if max(A) < min(B)
4647 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4648 if (Op1Min == Op0Max) // A >=s B -> A == B if max(A) == min(B)
4649 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0, Op1);
4650 break;
4651 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
4652 assert(!isa<ConstantInt>(Op1) && "ICMP_SLE with ConstantInt not folded!");
4653 if (Op0Max.sle(Op1Min)) // A <=s B -> true if max(A) <= min(B)
4654 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4655 if (Op0Min.sgt(Op1Max)) // A <=s B -> false if min(A) > max(B)
4656 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4657 if (Op1Max == Op0Min) // A <=s B -> A == B if min(A) == max(B)
4658 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0, Op1);
4659 break;
4660 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4661 assert(!isa<ConstantInt>(Op1) && "ICMP_UGE with ConstantInt not folded!");
4662 if (Op0Min.uge(Op1Max)) // A >=u B -> true if min(A) >= max(B)
4663 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4664 if (Op0Max.ult(Op1Min)) // A >=u B -> false if max(A) < min(B)
4665 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4666 if (Op1Min == Op0Max) // A >=u B -> A == B if max(A) == min(B)
4667 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0, Op1);
4668 break;
4669 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4670 assert(!isa<ConstantInt>(Op1) && "ICMP_ULE with ConstantInt not folded!");
4671 if (Op0Max.ule(Op1Min)) // A <=u B -> true if max(A) <= min(B)
4672 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getTrue(I.getType()));
4673 if (Op0Min.ugt(Op1Max)) // A <=u B -> false if min(A) > max(B)
4674 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, ConstantInt::getFalse(I.getType()));
4675 if (Op1Max == Op0Min) // A <=u B -> A == B if min(A) == max(B)
4676 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Op0, Op1);
4677 break;
4678 }
4679
4680 // Turn a signed comparison into an unsigned one if both operands are known to
4681 // have the same sign.
4682 if (I.isSigned() &&
4683 ((Op0Known.Zero.isNegative() && Op1Known.Zero.isNegative()) ||
4684 (Op0Known.One.isNegative() && Op1Known.One.isNegative())))
4685 return new ICmpInst(I.getUnsignedPredicate(), Op0, Op1);
4686
4687 return nullptr;
4688}
4689
4690/// If we have an icmp le or icmp ge instruction with a constant operand, turn
4691/// it into the appropriate icmp lt or icmp gt instruction. This transform
4692/// allows them to be folded in visitICmpInst.
4693static ICmpInst *canonicalizeCmpWithConstant(ICmpInst &I) {
4694 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
4695 if (Pred != ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE && Pred != ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE &&
4696 Pred != ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE && Pred != ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
4697 return nullptr;
4698
4699 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0);
4700 Value *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
4701 auto *Op1C = dyn_cast<Constant>(Op1);
4702 if (!Op1C)
4703 return nullptr;
4704
4705 // Check if the constant operand can be safely incremented/decremented without
4706 // overflowing/underflowing. For scalars, SimplifyICmpInst has already handled
4707 // the edge cases for us, so we just assert on them. For vectors, we must
4708 // handle the edge cases.
4709 Type *Op1Type = Op1->getType();
4710 bool IsSigned = I.isSigned();
4711 bool IsLE = (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE);
4712 auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op1C);
4713 if (CI) {
4714 // A <= MAX -> TRUE ; A >= MIN -> TRUE
4715 assert(IsLE ? !CI->isMaxValue(IsSigned) : !CI->isMinValue(IsSigned));
4716 } else if (Op1Type->isVectorTy()) {
4717 // TODO? If the edge cases for vectors were guaranteed to be handled as they
4718 // are for scalar, we could remove the min/max checks. However, to do that,
4719 // we would have to use insertelement/shufflevector to replace edge values.
4720 unsigned NumElts = Op1Type->getVectorNumElements();
4721 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i) {
4722 Constant *Elt = Op1C->getAggregateElement(i);
4723 if (!Elt)
4724 return nullptr;
4725
4726 if (isa<UndefValue>(Elt))
4727 continue;
4728
4729 // Bail out if we can't determine if this constant is min/max or if we
4730 // know that this constant is min/max.
4731 auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Elt);
4732 if (!CI || (IsLE ? CI->isMaxValue(IsSigned) : CI->isMinValue(IsSigned)))
4733 return nullptr;
4734 }
4735 } else {
4736 // ConstantExpr?
4737 return nullptr;
4738 }
4739
4740 // Increment or decrement the constant and set the new comparison predicate:
4741 // ULE -> ULT ; UGE -> UGT ; SLE -> SLT ; SGE -> SGT
4742 Constant *OneOrNegOne = ConstantInt::get(Op1Type, IsLE ? 1 : -1, true);
4743 CmpInst::Predicate NewPred = IsLE ? ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT: ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
4744 NewPred = IsSigned ? ICmpInst::getSignedPredicate(NewPred) : NewPred;
4745 return new ICmpInst(NewPred, Op0, ConstantExpr::getAdd(Op1C, OneOrNegOne));
4746}
4747
4748/// Integer compare with boolean values can always be turned into bitwise ops.
4749static Instruction *canonicalizeICmpBool(ICmpInst &I,
4750 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
4751 Value *A = I.getOperand(0), *B = I.getOperand(1);
4752 assert(A->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Bools only");
4753
4754 // A boolean compared to true/false can be simplified to Op0/true/false in
4755 // 14 out of the 20 (10 predicates * 2 constants) possible combinations.
4756 // Cases not handled by InstSimplify are always 'not' of Op0.
4757 if (match(B, m_Zero())) {
4758 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4759 case CmpInst::ICMP_EQ: // A == 0 -> !A
4760 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: // A <=u 0 -> !A
4761 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE: // A >=s 0 -> !A
4762 return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(A);
4763 default:
4764 llvm_unreachable("ICmp i1 X, C not simplified as expected.");
4765 }
4766 } else if (match(B, m_One())) {
4767 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4768 case CmpInst::ICMP_NE: // A != 1 -> !A
4769 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: // A <u 1 -> !A
4770 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: // A >s -1 -> !A
4771 return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(A);
4772 default:
4773 llvm_unreachable("ICmp i1 X, C not simplified as expected.");
4774 }
4775 }
4776
4777 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
4778 default:
4779 llvm_unreachable("Invalid icmp instruction!");
4780 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ:
4781 // icmp eq i1 A, B -> ~(A ^ B)
4782 return BinaryOperator::CreateNot(Builder.CreateXor(A, B));
4783
4784 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE:
4785 // icmp ne i1 A, B -> A ^ B
4786 return BinaryOperator::CreateXor(A, B);
4787
4788 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4789 // icmp ugt -> icmp ult
4790 std::swap(A, B);
4791 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4792 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4793 // icmp ult i1 A, B -> ~A & B
4794 return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(Builder.CreateNot(A), B);
4795
4796 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
4797 // icmp sgt -> icmp slt
4798 std::swap(A, B);
4799 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4800 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
4801 // icmp slt i1 A, B -> A & ~B
4802 return BinaryOperator::CreateAnd(Builder.CreateNot(B), A);
4803
4804 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4805 // icmp uge -> icmp ule
4806 std::swap(A, B);
4807 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4808 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4809 // icmp ule i1 A, B -> ~A | B
4810 return BinaryOperator::CreateOr(Builder.CreateNot(A), B);
4811
4812 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
4813 // icmp sge -> icmp sle
4814 std::swap(A, B);
4815 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4816 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
4817 // icmp sle i1 A, B -> A | ~B
4818 return BinaryOperator::CreateOr(Builder.CreateNot(B), A);
4819 }
4820}
4821
4822// Transform pattern like:
4823// (1 << Y) u<= X or ~(-1 << Y) u< X or ((1 << Y)+(-1)) u< X
4824// (1 << Y) u> X or ~(-1 << Y) u>= X or ((1 << Y)+(-1)) u>= X
4825// Into:
4826// (X l>> Y) != 0
4827// (X l>> Y) == 0
4828static Instruction *foldICmpWithHighBitMask(ICmpInst &Cmp,
4829 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
4830 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred, NewPred;
4831 Value *X, *Y;
4832 if (match(&Cmp,
4833 m_c_ICmp(Pred, m_OneUse(m_Shl(m_One(), m_Value(Y))), m_Value(X)))) {
4834 // We want X to be the icmp's second operand, so swap predicate if it isn't.
4835 if (Cmp.getOperand(0) == X)
4836 Pred = Cmp.getSwappedPredicate();
4837
4838 switch (Pred) {
4839 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
4840 NewPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
4841 break;
4842 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
4843 NewPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
4844 break;
4845 default:
4846 return nullptr;
4847 }
4848 } else if (match(&Cmp, m_c_ICmp(Pred,
4849 m_OneUse(m_CombineOr(
4850 m_Not(m_Shl(m_AllOnes(), m_Value(Y))),
4851 m_Add(m_Shl(m_One(), m_Value(Y)),
4852 m_AllOnes()))),
4853 m_Value(X)))) {
4854 // The variant with 'add' is not canonical, (the variant with 'not' is)
4855 // we only get it because it has extra uses, and can't be canonicalized,
4856
4857 // We want X to be the icmp's second operand, so swap predicate if it isn't.
4858 if (Cmp.getOperand(0) == X)
4859 Pred = Cmp.getSwappedPredicate();
4860
4861 switch (Pred) {
4862 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
4863 NewPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
4864 break;
4865 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
4866 NewPred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
4867 break;
4868 default:
4869 return nullptr;
4870 }
4871 } else
4872 return nullptr;
4873
4874 Value *NewX = Builder.CreateLShr(X, Y, X->getName() + ".highbits");
4875 Constant *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(NewX->getType());
4876 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, NewPred, NewX, Zero);
4877}
4878
4879static Instruction *foldVectorCmp(CmpInst &Cmp,
4880 InstCombiner::BuilderTy &Builder) {
4881 // If both arguments of the cmp are shuffles that use the same mask and
4882 // shuffle within a single vector, move the shuffle after the cmp.
4883 Value *LHS = Cmp.getOperand(0), *RHS = Cmp.getOperand(1);
4884 Value *V1, *V2;
4885 Constant *M;
4886 if (match(LHS, m_ShuffleVector(m_Value(V1), m_Undef(), m_Constant(M))) &&
4887 match(RHS, m_ShuffleVector(m_Value(V2), m_Undef(), m_Specific(M))) &&
4888 V1->getType() == V2->getType() &&
4889 (LHS->hasOneUse() || RHS->hasOneUse())) {
4890 // cmp (shuffle V1, M), (shuffle V2, M) --> shuffle (cmp V1, V2), M
4891 CmpInst::Predicate P = Cmp.getPredicate();
4892 Value *NewCmp = isa<ICmpInst>(Cmp) ? Builder.CreateICmp(P, V1, V2)
4893 : Builder.CreateFCmp(P, V1, V2);
4894 return new ShuffleVectorInst(NewCmp, UndefValue::get(NewCmp->getType()), M);
4895 }
4896 return nullptr;
4897}
4898
4899Instruction *InstCombiner::visitICmpInst(ICmpInst &I) {
4900 bool Changed = false;
4901 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
4902 unsigned Op0Cplxity = getComplexity(Op0);
4903 unsigned Op1Cplxity = getComplexity(Op1);
4904
4905 /// Orders the operands of the compare so that they are listed from most
4906 /// complex to least complex. This puts constants before unary operators,
4907 /// before binary operators.
4908 if (Op0Cplxity < Op1Cplxity ||
4909 (Op0Cplxity == Op1Cplxity && swapMayExposeCSEOpportunities(Op0, Op1))) {
4910 I.swapOperands();
4911 std::swap(Op0, Op1);
4912 Changed = true;
4913 }
4914
4915 if (Value *V = SimplifyICmpInst(I.getPredicate(), Op0, Op1,
4916 SQ.getWithInstruction(&I)))
4917 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, V);
4918
4919 // Comparing -val or val with non-zero is the same as just comparing val
4920 // ie, abs(val) != 0 -> val != 0
4921 if (I.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && match(Op1, m_Zero())) {
4922 Value *Cond, *SelectTrue, *SelectFalse;
4923 if (match(Op0, m_Select(m_Value(Cond), m_Value(SelectTrue),
4924 m_Value(SelectFalse)))) {
4925 if (Value *V = dyn_castNegVal(SelectTrue)) {
4926 if (V == SelectFalse)
4927 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, I.getPredicate(), V, Op1);
4928 }
4929 else if (Value *V = dyn_castNegVal(SelectFalse)) {
4930 if (V == SelectTrue)
4931 return CmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, I.getPredicate(), V, Op1);
4932 }
4933 }
4934 }
4935
4936 if (Op0->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1))
4937 if (Instruction *Res = canonicalizeICmpBool(I, Builder))
4938 return Res;
4939
4940 if (ICmpInst *NewICmp = canonicalizeCmpWithConstant(I))
4941 return NewICmp;
4942
4943 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpWithConstant(I))
4944 return Res;
4945
4946 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpWithDominatingICmp(I))
4947 return Res;
4948
4949 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpUsingKnownBits(I))
4950 return Res;
4951
4952 // Test if the ICmpInst instruction is used exclusively by a select as
4953 // part of a minimum or maximum operation. If so, refrain from doing
4954 // any other folding. This helps out other analyses which understand
4955 // non-obfuscated minimum and maximum idioms, such as ScalarEvolution
4956 // and CodeGen. And in this case, at least one of the comparison
4957 // operands has at least one user besides the compare (the select),
4958 // which would often largely negate the benefit of folding anyway.
4959 //
4960 // Do the same for the other patterns recognized by matchSelectPattern.
4961 if (I.hasOneUse())
4962 if (SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I.user_back())) {
4963 Value *A, *B;
4964 SelectPatternResult SPR = matchSelectPattern(SI, A, B);
4965 if (SPR.Flavor != SPF_UNKNOWN)
4966 return nullptr;
4967 }
4968
4969 // Do this after checking for min/max to prevent infinite looping.
4970 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpWithZero(I))
4971 return Res;
4972
4973 // FIXME: We only do this after checking for min/max to prevent infinite
4974 // looping caused by a reverse canonicalization of these patterns for min/max.
4975 // FIXME: The organization of folds is a mess. These would naturally go into
4976 // canonicalizeCmpWithConstant(), but we can't move all of the above folds
4977 // down here after the min/max restriction.
4978 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
4979 const APInt *C;
4980 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(C))) {
4981 // For i32: x >u 2147483647 -> x <s 0 -> true if sign bit set
4982 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT && C->isMaxSignedValue()) {
4983 Constant *Zero = Constant::getNullValue(Op0->getType());
4984 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT, Op0, Zero);
4985 }
4986
4987 // For i32: x <u 2147483648 -> x >s -1 -> true if sign bit clear
4988 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT && C->isMinSignedValue()) {
4989 Constant *AllOnes = Constant::getAllOnesValue(Op0->getType());
4990 return new ICmpInst(ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT, Op0, AllOnes);
4991 }
4992 }
4993
4994 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpInstWithConstant(I))
4995 return Res;
4996
4997 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpInstWithConstantNotInt(I))
4998 return Res;
4999
5000 // If we can optimize a 'icmp GEP, P' or 'icmp P, GEP', do so now.
5001 if (GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Op0))
5002 if (Instruction *NI = foldGEPICmp(GEP, Op1, I.getPredicate(), I))
5003 return NI;
5004 if (GEPOperator *GEP = dyn_cast<GEPOperator>(Op1))
5005 if (Instruction *NI = foldGEPICmp(GEP, Op0,
5006 ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(I.getPredicate()), I))
5007 return NI;
5008
5009 // Try to optimize equality comparisons against alloca-based pointers.
5010 if (Op0->getType()->isPointerTy() && I.isEquality()) {
5011 assert(Op1->getType()->isPointerTy() && "Comparing pointer with non-pointer?");
5012 if (auto *Alloca = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(GetUnderlyingObject(Op0, DL)))
5013 if (Instruction *New = foldAllocaCmp(I, Alloca, Op1))
5014 return New;
5015 if (auto *Alloca = dyn_cast<AllocaInst>(GetUnderlyingObject(Op1, DL)))
5016 if (Instruction *New = foldAllocaCmp(I, Alloca, Op0))
5017 return New;
5018 }
5019
5020 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpBitCast(I, Builder))
5021 return Res;
5022
5023 if (isa<CastInst>(Op0)) {
5024 // Handle the special case of: icmp (cast bool to X), <cst>
5025 // This comes up when you have code like
5026 // int X = A < B;
5027 // if (X) ...
5028 // For generality, we handle any zero-extension of any operand comparison
5029 // with a constant or another cast from the same type.
5030 if (isa<Constant>(Op1) || isa<CastInst>(Op1))
5031 if (Instruction *R = foldICmpWithCastAndCast(I))
5032 return R;
5033 }
5034
5035 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpBinOp(I))
5036 return Res;
5037
5038 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpWithMinMax(I))
5039 return Res;
5040
5041 {
5042 Value *A, *B;
5043 // Transform (A & ~B) == 0 --> (A & B) != 0
5044 // and (A & ~B) != 0 --> (A & B) == 0
5045 // if A is a power of 2.
5046 if (match(Op0, m_And(m_Value(A), m_Not(m_Value(B)))) &&
5047 match(Op1, m_Zero()) &&
5048 isKnownToBeAPowerOfTwo(A, false, 0, &I) && I.isEquality())
5049 return new ICmpInst(I.getInversePredicate(), Builder.CreateAnd(A, B),
5050 Op1);
5051
5052 // ~X < ~Y --> Y < X
5053 // ~X < C --> X > ~C
5054 if (match(Op0, m_Not(m_Value(A)))) {
5055 if (match(Op1, m_Not(m_Value(B))))
5056 return new ICmpInst(I.getPredicate(), B, A);
5057
5058 const APInt *C;
5059 if (match(Op1, m_APInt(C)))
5060 return new ICmpInst(I.getSwappedPredicate(), A,
5061 ConstantInt::get(Op1->getType(), ~(*C)));
5062 }
5063
5064 Instruction *AddI = nullptr;
5065 if (match(&I, m_UAddWithOverflow(m_Value(A), m_Value(B),
5066 m_Instruction(AddI))) &&
5067 isa<IntegerType>(A->getType())) {
5068 Value *Result;
5069 Constant *Overflow;
5070 if (OptimizeOverflowCheck(Instruction::Add, /*Signed*/false, A, B,
5071 *AddI, Result, Overflow)) {
5072 replaceInstUsesWith(*AddI, Result);
5073 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Overflow);
5074 }
5075 }
5076
5077 // (zext a) * (zext b) --> llvm.umul.with.overflow.
5078 if (match(Op0, m_Mul(m_ZExt(m_Value(A)), m_ZExt(m_Value(B))))) {
5079 if (Instruction *R = processUMulZExtIdiom(I, Op0, Op1, *this))
5080 return R;
5081 }
5082 if (match(Op1, m_Mul(m_ZExt(m_Value(A)), m_ZExt(m_Value(B))))) {
5083 if (Instruction *R = processUMulZExtIdiom(I, Op1, Op0, *this))
5084 return R;
5085 }
5086 }
5087
5088 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpEquality(I))
5089 return Res;
5090
5091 // The 'cmpxchg' instruction returns an aggregate containing the old value and
5092 // an i1 which indicates whether or not we successfully did the swap.
5093 //
5094 // Replace comparisons between the old value and the expected value with the
5095 // indicator that 'cmpxchg' returns.
5096 //
5097 // N.B. This transform is only valid when the 'cmpxchg' is not permitted to
5098 // spuriously fail. In those cases, the old value may equal the expected
5099 // value but it is possible for the swap to not occur.
5100 if (I.getPredicate() == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
5101 if (auto *EVI = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(Op0))
5102 if (auto *ACXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(EVI->getAggregateOperand()))
5103 if (EVI->getIndices()[0] == 0 && ACXI->getCompareOperand() == Op1 &&
5104 !ACXI->isWeak())
5105 return ExtractValueInst::Create(ACXI, 1);
5106
5107 {
5108 Value *X;
5109 const APInt *C;
5110 // icmp X+Cst, X
5111 if (match(Op0, m_Add(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C))) && Op1 == X)
5112 return foldICmpAddOpConst(X, *C, I.getPredicate());
5113
5114 // icmp X, X+Cst
5115 if (match(Op1, m_Add(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C))) && Op0 == X)
5116 return foldICmpAddOpConst(X, *C, I.getSwappedPredicate());
5117 }
5118
5119 if (Instruction *Res = foldICmpWithHighBitMask(I, Builder))
5120 return Res;
5121
5122 if (I.getType()->isVectorTy())
5123 if (Instruction *Res = foldVectorCmp(I, Builder))
5124 return Res;
5125
5126 return Changed ? &I : nullptr;
5127}
5128
5129/// Fold fcmp ([us]itofp x, cst) if possible.
5130Instruction *InstCombiner::foldFCmpIntToFPConst(FCmpInst &I, Instruction *LHSI,
5131 Constant *RHSC) {
5132 if (!isa<ConstantFP>(RHSC)) return nullptr;
5133 const APFloat &RHS = cast<ConstantFP>(RHSC)->getValueAPF();
5134
5135 // Get the width of the mantissa. We don't want to hack on conversions that
5136 // might lose information from the integer, e.g. "i64 -> float"
5137 int MantissaWidth = LHSI->getType()->getFPMantissaWidth();
5138 if (MantissaWidth == -1) return nullptr; // Unknown.
5139
5140 IntegerType *IntTy = cast<IntegerType>(LHSI->getOperand(0)->getType());
5141
5142 bool LHSUnsigned = isa<UIToFPInst>(LHSI);
5143
5144 if (I.isEquality()) {
5145 FCmpInst::Predicate P = I.getPredicate();
5146 bool IsExact = false;
5147 APSInt RHSCvt(IntTy->getBitWidth(), LHSUnsigned);
5148 RHS.convertToInteger(RHSCvt, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &IsExact);
5149
5150 // If the floating point constant isn't an integer value, we know if we will
5151 // ever compare equal / not equal to it.
5152 if (!IsExact) {
5153 // TODO: Can never be -0.0 and other non-representable values
5154 APFloat RHSRoundInt(RHS);
5155 RHSRoundInt.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5156 if (RHS.compare(RHSRoundInt) != APFloat::cmpEqual) {
5157 if (P == FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ || P == FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ)
5158 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5159
5160 assert(P == FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE || P == FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE);
5161 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5162 }
5163 }
5164
5165 // TODO: If the constant is exactly representable, is it always OK to do
5166 // equality compares as integer?
5167 }
5168
5169 // Check to see that the input is converted from an integer type that is small
5170 // enough that preserves all bits. TODO: check here for "known" sign bits.
5171 // This would allow us to handle (fptosi (x >>s 62) to float) if x is i64 f.e.
5172 unsigned InputSize = IntTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
5173
5174 // Following test does NOT adjust InputSize downwards for signed inputs,
5175 // because the most negative value still requires all the mantissa bits
5176 // to distinguish it from one less than that value.
5177 if ((int)InputSize > MantissaWidth) {
5178 // Conversion would lose accuracy. Check if loss can impact comparison.
5179 int Exp = ilogb(RHS);
5180 if (Exp == APFloat::IEK_Inf) {
5181 int MaxExponent = ilogb(APFloat::getLargest(RHS.getSemantics()));
5182 if (MaxExponent < (int)InputSize - !LHSUnsigned)
5183 // Conversion could create infinity.
5184 return nullptr;
5185 } else {
5186 // Note that if RHS is zero or NaN, then Exp is negative
5187 // and first condition is trivially false.
5188 if (MantissaWidth <= Exp && Exp <= (int)InputSize - !LHSUnsigned)
5189 // Conversion could affect comparison.
5190 return nullptr;
5191 }
5192 }
5193
5194 // Otherwise, we can potentially simplify the comparison. We know that it
5195 // will always come through as an integer value and we know the constant is
5196 // not a NAN (it would have been previously simplified).
5197 assert(!RHS.isNaN() && "NaN comparison not already folded!");
5198
5199 ICmpInst::Predicate Pred;
5200 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
5201 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected predicate!");
5202 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ:
5203 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ:
5204 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ;
5205 break;
5206 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5207 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5208 Pred = LHSUnsigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT : ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
5209 break;
5210 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5211 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
5212 Pred = LHSUnsigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE : ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE;
5213 break;
5214 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5215 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5216 Pred = LHSUnsigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT : ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
5217 break;
5218 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5219 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5220 Pred = LHSUnsigned ? ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE : ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE;
5221 break;
5222 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE:
5223 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE:
5224 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_NE;
5225 break;
5226 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD:
5227 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5228 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO:
5229 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5230 }
5231
5232 // Now we know that the APFloat is a normal number, zero or inf.
5233
5234 // See if the FP constant is too large for the integer. For example,
5235 // comparing an i8 to 300.0.
5236 unsigned IntWidth = IntTy->getScalarSizeInBits();
5237
5238 if (!LHSUnsigned) {
5239 // If the RHS value is > SignedMax, fold the comparison. This handles +INF
5240 // and large values.
5241 APFloat SMax(RHS.getSemantics());
5242 SMax.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getSignedMaxValue(IntWidth), true,
5243 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5244 if (SMax.compare(RHS) == APFloat::cmpLessThan) { // smax < 13123.0
5245 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT ||
5246 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
5247 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5248 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5249 }
5250 } else {
5251 // If the RHS value is > UnsignedMax, fold the comparison. This handles
5252 // +INF and large values.
5253 APFloat UMax(RHS.getSemantics());
5254 UMax.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getMaxValue(IntWidth), false,
5255 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5256 if (UMax.compare(RHS) == APFloat::cmpLessThan) { // umax < 13123.0
5257 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT ||
5258 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
5259 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5260 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5261 }
5262 }
5263
5264 if (!LHSUnsigned) {
5265 // See if the RHS value is < SignedMin.
5266 APFloat SMin(RHS.getSemantics());
5267 SMin.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getSignedMinValue(IntWidth), true,
5268 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5269 if (SMin.compare(RHS) == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan) { // smin > 12312.0
5270 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT ||
5271 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
5272 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5273 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5274 }
5275 } else {
5276 // See if the RHS value is < UnsignedMin.
5277 APFloat SMin(RHS.getSemantics());
5278 SMin.convertFromAPInt(APInt::getMinValue(IntWidth), true,
5279 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
5280 if (SMin.compare(RHS) == APFloat::cmpGreaterThan) { // umin > 12312.0
5281 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT ||
5282 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
5283 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5284 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5285 }
5286 }
5287
5288 // Okay, now we know that the FP constant fits in the range [SMIN, SMAX] or
5289 // [0, UMAX], but it may still be fractional. See if it is fractional by
5290 // casting the FP value to the integer value and back, checking for equality.
5291 // Don't do this for zero, because -0.0 is not fractional.
5292 Constant *RHSInt = LHSUnsigned
5293 ? ConstantExpr::getFPToUI(RHSC, IntTy)
5294 : ConstantExpr::getFPToSI(RHSC, IntTy);
5295 if (!RHS.isZero()) {
5296 bool Equal = LHSUnsigned
5297 ? ConstantExpr::getUIToFP(RHSInt, RHSC->getType()) == RHSC
5298 : ConstantExpr::getSIToFP(RHSInt, RHSC->getType()) == RHSC;
5299 if (!Equal) {
5300 // If we had a comparison against a fractional value, we have to adjust
5301 // the compare predicate and sometimes the value. RHSC is rounded towards
5302 // zero at this point.
5303 switch (Pred) {
5304 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected integer comparison!");
5305 case ICmpInst::ICMP_NE: // (float)int != 4.4 --> true
5306 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5307 case ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ: // (float)int == 4.4 --> false
5308 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5309 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
5310 // (float)int <= 4.4 --> int <= 4
5311 // (float)int <= -4.4 --> false
5312 if (RHS.isNegative())
5313 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5314 break;
5315 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
5316 // (float)int <= 4.4 --> int <= 4
5317 // (float)int <= -4.4 --> int < -4
5318 if (RHS.isNegative())
5319 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
5320 break;
5321 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
5322 // (float)int < -4.4 --> false
5323 // (float)int < 4.4 --> int <= 4
5324 if (RHS.isNegative())
5325 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getFalse());
5326 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE;
5327 break;
5328 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
5329 // (float)int < -4.4 --> int < -4
5330 // (float)int < 4.4 --> int <= 4
5331 if (!RHS.isNegative())
5332 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE;
5333 break;
5334 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
5335 // (float)int > 4.4 --> int > 4
5336 // (float)int > -4.4 --> true
5337 if (RHS.isNegative())
5338 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5339 break;
5340 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
5341 // (float)int > 4.4 --> int > 4
5342 // (float)int > -4.4 --> int >= -4
5343 if (RHS.isNegative())
5344 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE;
5345 break;
5346 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
5347 // (float)int >= -4.4 --> true
5348 // (float)int >= 4.4 --> int > 4
5349 if (RHS.isNegative())
5350 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, Builder.getTrue());
5351 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
5352 break;
5353 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
5354 // (float)int >= -4.4 --> int >= -4
5355 // (float)int >= 4.4 --> int > 4
5356 if (!RHS.isNegative())
5357 Pred = ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
5358 break;
5359 }
5360 }
5361 }
5362
5363 // Lower this FP comparison into an appropriate integer version of the
5364 // comparison.
5365 return new ICmpInst(Pred, LHSI->getOperand(0), RHSInt);
5366}

5368/// Fold (C / X) < 0.0 --> X < 0.0 if possible. Swap predicate if necessary.
5369static Instruction *foldFCmpReciprocalAndZero(FCmpInst &I, Instruction *LHSI,
5370 Constant *RHSC) {
5371 // When C is not 0.0 and infinities are not allowed:
5372 // (C / X) < 0.0 is a sign-bit test of X
5373 // (C / X) < 0.0 --> X < 0.0 (if C is positive)
5374 // (C / X) < 0.0 --> X > 0.0 (if C is negative, swap the predicate)
5375 //
5376 // Proof:
5377 // Multiply (C / X) < 0.0 by X * X / C.
5378 // - X is non zero, if it is the flag 'ninf' is violated.
5379 // - C defines the sign of X * X * C. Thus it also defines whether to swap
5380 // the predicate. C is also non zero by definition.
5381 //
5382 // Thus X * X / C is non zero and the transformation is valid. [qed]
5383
5384 FCmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
5385
5386 // Check that predicates are valid.
5387 if ((Pred != FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT) && (Pred != FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT) &&
5388 (Pred != FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE) && (Pred != FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE))
5389 return nullptr;
5390
5391 // Check that RHS operand is zero.
5392 if (!match(RHSC, m_AnyZeroFP()))
5393 return nullptr;
5394
5395 // Check fastmath flags ('ninf').
5396 if (!LHSI->hasNoInfs() || !I.hasNoInfs())
5397 return nullptr;
5398
5399 // Check the properties of the dividend. It must not be zero to avoid a
5400 // division by zero (see Proof).
5401 const APFloat *C;
5402 if (!match(LHSI->getOperand(0), m_APFloat(C)))
5403 return nullptr;
5404
5405 if (C->isZero())
5406 return nullptr;
5407
5408 // Get swapped predicate if necessary.
5409 if (C->isNegative())
5410 Pred = I.getSwappedPredicate();
5411
5412 return new FCmpInst(Pred, LHSI->getOperand(1), RHSC, "", &I);
5413}
5414
5415/// Optimize fabs(X) compared with zero.
5416static Instruction *foldFabsWithFcmpZero(FCmpInst &I) {
5417 Value *X;
5418 if (!match(I.getOperand(0), m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::fabs>(m_Value(X))) ||
5419 !match(I.getOperand(1), m_PosZeroFP()))
5420 return nullptr;
5421
5422 auto replacePredAndOp0 = [](FCmpInst *I, FCmpInst::Predicate P, Value *X) {
5423 I->setPredicate(P);
5424 I->setOperand(0, X);
5425 return I;
5426 };
5427
5428 switch (I.getPredicate()) {
5429 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5430 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5431 // fabs(X) >= 0.0 --> true
5432 // fabs(X) < 0.0 --> false
5433 llvm_unreachable("fcmp should have simplified");
5434
5435 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5436 // fabs(X) > 0.0 --> X != 0.0
5437 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE, X);
5438
5439 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5440 // fabs(X) u> 0.0 --> X u!= 0.0
5441 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE, X);
5442
5443 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
5444 // fabs(X) <= 0.0 --> X == 0.0
5445 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ, X);
5446
5447 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5448 // fabs(X) u<= 0.0 --> X u== 0.0
5449 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ, X);
5450
5451 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
5452 // fabs(X) >= 0.0 --> !isnan(X)
5453 assert(!I.hasNoNaNs() && "fcmp should have simplified");
5454 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD, X);
5455
5456 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5457 // fabs(X) u< 0.0 --> isnan(X)
5458 assert(!I.hasNoNaNs() && "fcmp should have simplified");
5459 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO, X);
5460
5461 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ:
5462 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UEQ:
5463 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ONE:
5464 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE:
5465 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD:
5466 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO:
5467 // Look through the fabs() because it doesn't change anything but the sign.
5468 // fabs(X) == 0.0 --> X == 0.0,
5469 // fabs(X) != 0.0 --> X != 0.0
5470 // isnan(fabs(X)) --> isnan(X)
5471 // !isnan(fabs(X) --> !isnan(X)
5472 return replacePredAndOp0(&I, I.getPredicate(), X);
5473
5474 default:
5475 return nullptr;
5476 }
5477}
5478
5479Instruction *InstCombiner::visitFCmpInst(FCmpInst &I) {
5480 bool Changed = false;
5481
5482 /// Orders the operands of the compare so that they are listed from most
5483 /// complex to least complex. This puts constants before unary operators,
5484 /// before binary operators.
5485 if (getComplexity(I.getOperand(0)) < getComplexity(I.getOperand(1))) {
5486 I.swapOperands();
5487 Changed = true;
5488 }
5489
5490 const CmpInst::Predicate Pred = I.getPredicate();
5491 Value *Op0 = I.getOperand(0), *Op1 = I.getOperand(1);
5492 if (Value *V = SimplifyFCmpInst(Pred, Op0, Op1, I.getFastMathFlags(),
5493 SQ.getWithInstruction(&I)))
5494 return replaceInstUsesWith(I, V);
5495
5496 // Simplify 'fcmp pred X, X'
5497 Type *OpType = Op0->getType();
5498 assert(OpType == Op1->getType() && "fcmp with different-typed operands?");
5499 if (Op0 == Op1) {
5500 switch (Pred) {
5501 default: break;
5502 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO: // True if unordered: isnan(X) | isnan(Y)
5503 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT: // True if unordered or less than
5504 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT: // True if unordered or greater than
5505 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UNE: // True if unordered or not equal
5506 // Canonicalize these to be 'fcmp uno %X, 0.0'.
5507 I.setPredicate(FCmpInst::FCMP_UNO);
5508 I.setOperand(1, Constant::getNullValue(OpType));
5509 return &I;
5510
5511 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD: // True if ordered (no nans)
5512 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OEQ: // True if ordered and equal
5513 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: // True if ordered and greater than or equal
5514 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: // True if ordered and less than or equal
5515 // Canonicalize these to be 'fcmp ord %X, 0.0'.
5516 I.setPredicate(FCmpInst::FCMP_ORD);
5517 I.setOperand(1, Constant::getNullValue(OpType));
5518 return &I;
5519 }
5520 }
5521
5522 // If we're just checking for a NaN (ORD/UNO) and have a non-NaN operand,
5523 // then canonicalize the operand to 0.0.
5524 if (Pred == CmpInst::FCMP_ORD || Pred == CmpInst::FCMP_UNO) {
5525 if (!match(Op0, m_PosZeroFP()) && isKnownNeverNaN(Op0, &TLI)) {
5526 I.setOperand(0, ConstantFP::getNullValue(OpType));
5527 return &I;
5528 }
5529 if (!match(Op1, m_PosZeroFP()) && isKnownNeverNaN(Op1, &TLI)) {
5530 I.setOperand(1, ConstantFP::getNullValue(OpType));
5531 return &I;
5532 }
5533 }
5534
5535 // fcmp pred (fneg X), (fneg Y) -> fcmp swap(pred) X, Y
5536 Value *X, *Y;
5537 if (match(Op0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(Op1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Y))))
5538 return new FCmpInst(I.getSwappedPredicate(), X, Y, "", &I);
5539
5540 // Test if the FCmpInst instruction is used exclusively by a select as
5541 // part of a minimum or maximum operation. If so, refrain from doing
5542 // any other folding. This helps out other analyses which understand
5543 // non-obfuscated minimum and maximum idioms, such as ScalarEvolution
5544 // and CodeGen. And in this case, at least one of the comparison
5545 // operands has at least one user besides the compare (the select),
5546 // which would often largely negate the benefit of folding anyway.
5547 if (I.hasOneUse())
5548 if (SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(I.user_back())) {
5549 Value *A, *B;
5550 SelectPatternResult SPR = matchSelectPattern(SI, A, B);
5551 if (SPR.Flavor != SPF_UNKNOWN)
5552 return nullptr;
5553 }
5554
5555 // The sign of 0.0 is ignored by fcmp, so canonicalize to +0.0:
5556 // fcmp Pred X, -0.0 --> fcmp Pred X, 0.0
5557 if (match(Op1, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(Op1, m_PosZeroFP())) {
5558 I.setOperand(1, ConstantFP::getNullValue(OpType));
5559 return &I;
5560 }
5561
5562 // Handle fcmp with instruction LHS and constant RHS.
5563 Instruction *LHSI;
5564 Constant *RHSC;
5565 if (match(Op0, m_Instruction(LHSI)) && match(Op1, m_Constant(RHSC))) {
5566 switch (LHSI->getOpcode()) {
5567 case Instruction::PHI:
5568 // Only fold fcmp into the PHI if the phi and fcmp are in the same
5569 // block. If in the same block, we're encouraging jump threading. If
5570 // not, we are just pessimizing the code by making an i1 phi.
5571 if (LHSI->getParent() == I.getParent())
5572 if (Instruction *NV = foldOpIntoPhi(I, cast<PHINode>(LHSI)))
5573 return NV;
5574 break;
5575 case Instruction::SIToFP:
5576 case Instruction::UIToFP:
5577 if (Instruction *NV = foldFCmpIntToFPConst(I, LHSI, RHSC))
5578 return NV;
5579 break;
5580 case Instruction::FDiv:
5581 if (Instruction *NV = foldFCmpReciprocalAndZero(I, LHSI, RHSC))
5582 return NV;
5583 break;
5584 case Instruction::Load:
5585 if (auto *GEP = dyn_cast<GetElementPtrInst>(LHSI->getOperand(0)))
5586 if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GEP->getOperand(0)))
5587 if (GV->isConstant() && GV->hasDefinitiveInitializer() &&
5588 !cast<LoadInst>(LHSI)->isVolatile())
5589 if (Instruction *Res = foldCmpLoadFromIndexedGlobal(GEP, GV, I))
5590 return Res;
5591 break;
5592 }
5593 }
5594
5595 if (Instruction *R = foldFabsWithFcmpZero(I))
5596 return R;
5597
5598 if (match(Op0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X)))) {
5599 // fcmp pred (fneg X), C --> fcmp swap(pred) X, -C
5600 Constant *C;
5601 if (match(Op1, m_Constant(C))) {
5602 Constant *NegC = ConstantExpr::getFNeg(C);
5603 return new FCmpInst(I.getSwappedPredicate(), X, NegC, "", &I);
5604 }
5605 }
5606
5607 if (match(Op0, m_FPExt(m_Value(X)))) {
5608 // fcmp (fpext X), (fpext Y) -> fcmp X, Y
5609 if (match(Op1, m_FPExt(m_Value(Y))) && X->getType() == Y->getType())
5610 return new FCmpInst(Pred, X, Y, "", &I);
5611
5612 // fcmp (fpext X), C -> fcmp X, (fptrunc C) if fptrunc is lossless
5613 const APFloat *C;
5614 if (match(Op1, m_APFloat(C))) {
5615 const fltSemantics &FPSem =
5616 X->getType()->getScalarType()->getFltSemantics();
5617 bool Lossy;
5618 APFloat TruncC = *C;
5619 TruncC.convert(FPSem, APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &Lossy);
5620
5621 // Avoid lossy conversions and denormals.
5622 // Zero is a special case that's OK to convert.
5623 APFloat Fabs = TruncC;
5624 Fabs.clearSign();
5625 if (!Lossy &&
5626 ((Fabs.compare(APFloat::getSmallestNormalized(FPSem)) !=
5627 APFloat::cmpLessThan) || Fabs.isZero())) {
5628 Constant *NewC = ConstantFP::get(X->getType(), TruncC);
5629 return new FCmpInst(Pred, X, NewC, "", &I);
5630 }
5631 }
5632 }
5633
5634 if (I.getType()->isVectorTy())
5635 if (Instruction *Res = foldVectorCmp(I, Builder))
5636 return Res;
5637
5638 return Changed ? &I : nullptr;
5639}
